4076  //static const char* escaped = "\"\\/\b\f\n\r\t";
4077  struct Parser
4078  {
4079  Parser(char* data, size_t /*size*/)
4080  : data(data)
4081  {
4082  }
4083 
4084  bool consume(char c)
4085  {
4086  if (crow_json_unlikely(*data != c))
4087  return false;
4088  data++;
4089  return true;
4090  }
4091 
4092  void ws_skip()
4093  {
4094  while(*data == ' ' || *data == '\t' || *data == '\r' || *data == '\n') ++data;
4095  };
4096 
4097  rvalue decode_string()
4098  {
4099  if (crow_json_unlikely(!consume('"')))
4100  return {};
4101  char* start = data;
4102  uint8_t has_escaping = 0;
4103  while(1)
4104  {
4105  if (crow_json_likely(*data != '"' && *data != '\\' && *data != '\0'))
4106  {
4107  data ++;
4108  }
4109  else if (*data == '"')
4110  {
4111  *data = 0;
4112  *(start-1) = has_escaping;
4113  data++;
4114  return {type::String, start, data-1};
4115  }
4116  else if (*data == '\\')
4117  {
4118  has_escaping = 1;
4119  data++;
4120  switch(*data)
4121  {
4122  case 'u':
4123  {
4124  auto check = [](char c)
4125  {
4126  return
4127  ('0' <= c && c <= '9') ||
4128  ('a' <= c && c <= 'f') ||
4129  ('A' <= c && c <= 'F');
4130  };
4131  if (!(check(*(data+1)) &&
4132  check(*(data+2)) &&
4133  check(*(data+3)) &&
4134  check(*(data+4))))
4135  return {};
4136  }
4137  data += 5;
4138  break;
4139  case '"':
4140  case '\\':
4141  case '/':
4142  case 'b':
4143  case 'f':
4144  case 'n':
4145  case 'r':
4146  case 't':
4147  data ++;
4148  break;
4149  default:
4150  return {};
4151  }
4152  }
4153  else
4154  return {};
4155  }
4156  return {};
4157  }
4158 
4159  rvalue decode_list()
4160  {
4161  rvalue ret(type::List);
4162  if (crow_json_unlikely(!consume('[')))
4163  {
4164  ret.set_error();
4165  return ret;
4166  }
4167  ws_skip();
4168  if (crow_json_unlikely(*data == ']'))
4169  {
4170  data++;
4171  return ret;
4172  }
4173 
4174  while(1)
4175  {
4176  auto v = decode_value();
4177  if (crow_json_unlikely(!v))
4178  {
4179  ret.set_error();
4180  break;
4181  }
4182  ws_skip();
4183  ret.emplace_back(std::move(v));
4184  if (*data == ']')
4185  {
4186  data++;
4187  break;
4188  }
4189  if (crow_json_unlikely(!consume(',')))
4190  {
4191  ret.set_error();
4192  break;
4193  }
4194  ws_skip();
4195  }
4196  return ret;
4197  }
4198 
4199  rvalue decode_number()
4200  {
4201  char* start = data;
4202 
4203  enum NumberParsingState
4204  {
4205  Minus,
4206  AfterMinus,
4207  ZeroFirst,
4208  Digits,
4209  DigitsAfterPoints,
4210  E,
4211  DigitsAfterE,
4212  Invalid,
4213  } state{Minus};
4214  while(crow_json_likely(state != Invalid))
4215  {
4216  switch(*data)
4217  {
4218  case '0':
4219  state = (NumberParsingState)"\2\2\7\3\4\6\6"[state];
4220  /*if (state == NumberParsingState::Minus || state == NumberParsingState::AfterMinus)
4221  {
4222  state = NumberParsingState::ZeroFirst;
4223  }
4224  else if (state == NumberParsingState::Digits ||
4225  state == NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterE ||
4226  state == NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterPoints)
4227  {
4228  // ok; pass
4229  }
4230  else if (state == NumberParsingState::E)
4231  {
4232  state = NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterE;
4233  }
4234  else
4235  return {};*/
4236  break;
4237  case '1': case '2': case '3':
4238  case '4': case '5': case '6':
4239  case '7': case '8': case '9':
4240  state = (NumberParsingState)"\3\3\7\3\4\6\6"[state];
4241  while(*(data+1) >= '0' && *(data+1) <= '9') data++;
4242  /*if (state == NumberParsingState::Minus || state == NumberParsingState::AfterMinus)
4243  {
4244  state = NumberParsingState::Digits;
4245  }
4246  else if (state == NumberParsingState::Digits ||
4247  state == NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterE ||
4248  state == NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterPoints)
4249  {
4250  // ok; pass
4251  }
4252  else if (state == NumberParsingState::E)
4253  {
4254  state = NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterE;
4255  }
4256  else
4257  return {};*/
4258  break;
4259  case '.':
4260  state = (NumberParsingState)"\7\7\4\4\7\7\7"[state];
4261  /*
4262  if (state == NumberParsingState::Digits || state == NumberParsingState::ZeroFirst)
4263  {
4264  state = NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterPoints;
4265  }
4266  else
4267  return {};
4268  */
4269  break;
4270  case '-':
4271  state = (NumberParsingState)"\1\7\7\7\7\6\7"[state];
4272  /*if (state == NumberParsingState::Minus)
4273  {
4274  state = NumberParsingState::AfterMinus;
4275  }
4276  else if (state == NumberParsingState::E)
4277  {
4278  state = NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterE;
4279  }
4280  else
4281  return {};*/
4282  break;
4283  case '+':
4284  state = (NumberParsingState)"\7\7\7\7\7\6\7"[state];
4285  /*if (state == NumberParsingState::E)
4286  {
4287  state = NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterE;
4288  }
4289  else
4290  return {};*/
4291  break;
4292  case 'e': case 'E':
4293  state = (NumberParsingState)"\7\7\7\5\5\7\7"[state];
4294  /*if (state == NumberParsingState::Digits ||
4295  state == NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterPoints)
4296  {
4297  state = NumberParsingState::E;
4298  }
4299  else
4300  return {};*/
4301  break;
4302  default:
4303  if (crow_json_likely(state == NumberParsingState::ZeroFirst ||
4304  state == NumberParsingState::Digits ||
4305  state == NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterPoints ||
4306  state == NumberParsingState::DigitsAfterE))
4307  return {type::Number, start, data};
4308  else
4309  return {};
4310  }
4311  data++;
4312  }
4313 
4314  return {};
4315  }
4316 
4317  rvalue decode_value()
4318  {
4319  switch(*data)
4320  {
4321  case '[':
4322  return decode_list();
4323  case '{':
4324  return decode_object();
4325  case '"':
4326  return decode_string();
4327  case 't':
4328  if (//e-data >= 4 &&
4329  data[1] == 'r' &&
4330  data[2] == 'u' &&
4331  data[3] == 'e')
4332  {
4333  data += 4;
4334  return {type::True};
4335  }
4336  else
4337  return {};
4338  case 'f':
4339  if (//e-data >= 5 &&
4340  data[1] == 'a' &&
4341  data[2] == 'l' &&
4342  data[3] == 's' &&
4343  data[4] == 'e')
4344  {
4345  data += 5;
4346  return {type::False};
4347  }
4348  else
4349  return {};
4350  case 'n':
4351  if (//e-data >= 4 &&
4352  data[1] == 'u' &&
4353  data[2] == 'l' &&
4354  data[3] == 'l')
4355  {
4356  data += 4;
4357  return {type::Null};
4358  }
4359  else
4360  return {};
4361  //case '1': case '2': case '3':
4362  //case '4': case '5': case '6':
4363  //case '7': case '8': case '9':
4364  //case '0': case '-':
4365  default:
4366  return decode_number();
4367  }
4368  return {};
4369  }
4370 
4371  rvalue decode_object()
4372  {
4373  rvalue ret(type::Object);
4374  if (crow_json_unlikely(!consume('{')))
4375  {
4376  ret.set_error();
4377  return ret;
4378  }
4379 
4380  ws_skip();
4381 
4382  if (crow_json_unlikely(*data == '}'))
4383  {
4384  data++;
4385  return ret;
4386  }
4387 
4388  while(1)
4389  {
4390  auto t = decode_string();
4391  if (crow_json_unlikely(!t))
4392  {
4393  ret.set_error();
4394  break;
4395  }
4396 
4397  ws_skip();
4398  if (crow_json_unlikely(!consume(':')))
4399  {
4400  ret.set_error();
4401  break;
4402  }
4403 
4404  // TODO caching key to speed up (flyweight?)
4405  auto key = t.s();
4406 
4407  ws_skip();
4408  auto v = decode_value();
4409  if (crow_json_unlikely(!v))
4410  {
4411  ret.set_error();
4412  break;
4413  }
4414  ws_skip();
4415 
4416  v.key_ = std::move(key);
4417  ret.emplace_back(std::move(v));
4418  if (crow_json_unlikely(*data == '}'))
4419  {
4420  data++;
4421  break;
4422  }
4423  if (crow_json_unlikely(!consume(',')))
4424  {
4425  ret.set_error();
4426  break;
4427  }
4428  ws_skip();
4429  }
4430  return ret;
4431  }
4432 
4433  rvalue parse()
4434  {
4435  ws_skip();
4436  auto ret = decode_value(); // or decode object?
4437  ws_skip();
4438  if (ret && *data != '\0')
4439  ret.set_error();
4440  return ret;
4441  }
4442 
4443  char* data;
4444  };
4445  return Parser(data, size).parse();
4446  }
4447  inline rvalue load(const char* data, size_t size)
4448  {
4449  char* s = new char[size+1];
4450  memcpy(s, data, size);
4451  s[size] = 0;
4452  auto ret = load_nocopy_internal(s, size);
4453  if (ret)
4454  ret.key_.force(s, size);
4455  else
4456  delete[] s;
4457  return ret;
4458  }
4459 
4460  inline rvalue load(const char* data)
4461  {
4462  return load(data, strlen(data));
4463  }
4464 
4465  inline rvalue load(const std::string& str)
4466  {
4467  return load(str.data(), str.size());
4468  }

4470  class wvalue
4471  {
4472  friend class crow::mustache::template_t;
4473  public:
4474  type t() const { return t_; }
4475  private:
4476  type t_{type::Null};
4477  double d {};
4478  std::string s;
4479  std::unique_ptr<std::vector<wvalue>> l;
4480  std::unique_ptr<std::unordered_map<std::string, wvalue>> o;
4481  public:
4482 
4483  wvalue() {}
4484 
4485  wvalue(const rvalue& r)
4486  {
4487  t_ = r.t();
4488  switch(r.t())
4489  {
4490  case type::Null:
4491  case type::False:
4492  case type::True:
4493  return;
4494  case type::Number:
4495  d = r.d();
4496  return;
4497  case type::String:
4498  s = r.s();
4499  return;
4500  case type::List:
4501  l = std::unique_ptr<std::vector<wvalue>>(new std::vector<wvalue>{});
4502  l->reserve(r.size());
4503  for(auto it = r.begin(); it != r.end(); ++it)
4504  l->emplace_back(*it);
4505  return;
4506  case type::Object:
4507  o = std::unique_ptr<
4508  std::unordered_map<std::string, wvalue>
4509  >(
4510  new std::unordered_map<std::string, wvalue>{});
4511  for(auto it = r.begin(); it != r.end(); ++it)
4512  o->emplace(it->key(), *it);
4513  return;
4514  }
4515  }
4516

4518  {
4519  *this = std::move(r);
4520  }

4649  template <typename T>
4650  wvalue& operator=(const std::vector<T>& v)
4651  {
4652  if (t_ != type::List)
4653  reset();
4654  t_ = type::List;
4655  if (!l)
4656  l = std::unique_ptr<std::vector<wvalue>>(new std::vector<wvalue>{});
4657  l->clear();
4658  l->resize(v.size());
4659  size_t idx = 0;
4660  for(auto& x:v)
4661  {
4662  (*l)[idx++] = x;
4663  }
4664  return *this;
4665  }

4673  l = std::unique_ptr<std::vector<wvalue>>(new std::vector<wvalue>{});
4674  if (l->size() < index+1)
4675  l->resize(index+1);
4676  return (*l)[index];

4694  o = std::unique_ptr<

4700 
4701  size_t estimate_length() const
4702  {
4703  switch(t_)
4704  {
4705  case type::Null: return 4;
4706  case type::False: return 5;
4707  case type::True: return 4;
4708  case type::Number: return 30;
4709  case type::String: return 2+s.size()+s.size()/2;
4710  case type::List:
4711  {
4712  size_t sum{};
4713  if (l)
4714  {
4715  for(auto& x:*l)
4716  {
4717  sum += 1;
4718  sum += x.estimate_length();
4719  }
4720  }
4721  return sum+2;
4722  }
4723  case type::Object:
4724  {
4725  size_t sum{};
4726  if (o)
4727  {
4728  for(auto& kv:*o)
4729  {
4730  sum += 2;
4731  sum += 2+kv.first.size()+kv.first.size()/2;
4732  sum += kv.second.estimate_length();
4733  }
4734  }
4735  return sum+2;
4736  }
4737  }
4738  return 1;
4739  }

4742  friend void dump_internal(const wvalue& v, std::string& out);
4743  friend std::string dump(const wvalue& v);
4744  };
4745 
4746  inline void dump_string(const std::string& str, std::string& out)
4747  {
4748  out.push_back('"');
4749  escape(str, out);
4750  out.push_back('"');
4751  }
4752  inline void dump_internal(const wvalue& v, std::string& out)
4753  {
4754  switch(v.t_)
4755  {
4756  case type::Null: out += "null"; break;
4757  case type::False: out += "false"; break;
4758  case type::True: out += "true"; break;
4759  case type::Number:
4760  {
4761  char outbuf[128];
4762  sprintf(outbuf, "%g", v.d);
4763  out += outbuf;
4764  }
4765  break;
4766  case type::String: dump_string(v.s, out); break;
4767  case type::List:
4768  {
4769  out.push_back('[');
4770  if (v.l)
4771  {
4772  bool first = true;
4773  for(auto& x:*v.l)
4774  {
4775  if (!first)
4776  {
4777  out.push_back(',');
4778  }
4779  first = false;
4780  dump_internal(x, out);
4781  }
4782  }
4783  out.push_back(']');
4784  }
4785  break;
4786  case type::Object:
4787  {
4788  out.push_back('{');
4789  if (v.o)
4790  {
4791  bool first = true;
4792  for(auto& kv:*v.o)
4793  {
4794  if (!first)
4795  {
4796  out.push_back(',');
4797  }
4798  first = false;
4799  dump_string(kv.first, out);
4800  out.push_back(':');
4801  dump_internal(kv.second, out);
4802  }
4803  }
4804  out.push_back('}');
4805  }
4806  break;
4807  }
4808  }
4809 
4810  inline std::string dump(const wvalue& v)
4811  {
4812  std::string ret;
4813  ret.reserve(v.estimate_length());
4814  dump_internal(v, ret);
4815  return ret;
4816  }

4819  //{
4820  //}
4821  }

4896  auto find_context(const std::string& name, const std::vector<context*>& stack)->std::pair<bool, context&>
4897  {
4898  if (name == ".")
4899  {
4900  return {true, *stack.back()};
4901  }
4902  int dotPosition = name.find(".");
4903  if (dotPosition == (int)name.npos)
4904  {
4905  for(auto it = stack.rbegin(); it != stack.rend(); ++it)
4906  {
4907  if ((*it)->t() == json::type::Object)
4908  {
4909  if ((*it)->count(name))
4910  return {true, (**it)[name]};
4911  }
4912  }
4913  }
4914  else
4915  {
4916  std::vector<int> dotPositions;
4917  dotPositions.push_back(-1);
4918  while(dotPosition != (int)name.npos)
4919  {
4920  dotPositions.push_back(dotPosition);
4921  dotPosition = name.find(".", dotPosition+1);
4922  }
4923  dotPositions.push_back(name.size());
4924  std::vector<std::string> names;
4925  names.reserve(dotPositions.size()-1);
4926  for(int i = 1; i < (int)dotPositions.size(); i ++)
4927  names.emplace_back(name.substr(dotPositions[i-1]+1, dotPositions[i]-dotPositions[i-1]-1));
4928 
4929  for(auto it = stack.rbegin(); it != stack.rend(); ++it)
4930  {
4931  context* view = *it;
4932  bool found = true;
4933  for(auto jt = names.begin(); jt != names.end(); ++jt)
4934  {
4935  if (view->t() == json::type::Object &&
4936  view->count(*jt))
4937  {
4938  view = &(*view)[*jt];
4939  }
4940  else
4941  {
4942  found = false;
4943  break;
4944  }
4945  }
4946  if (found)
4947  return {true, *view};
4948  }
4949 
4950  }
4951 
4952  static json::wvalue empty_str;
4953  empty_str = "";
4954  return {false, empty_str};
4955  }
4956 
4957  void escape(const std::string& in, std::string& out)
4958  {
4959  out.reserve(out.size() + in.size());
4960  for(auto it = in.begin(); it != in.end(); ++it)
4961  {
4962  switch(*it)
4963  {
4964  case '&': out += "&amp;"; break;
4965  case '<': out += "&lt;"; break;
4966  case '>': out += "&gt;"; break;
4967  case '"': out += "&quot;"; break;
4968  case '\'': out += "&#39;"; break;
4969  case '/': out += "&#x2F;"; break;
4970  default: out += *it; break;
4971  }
4972  }
4973  }
4974 
4975  void render_internal(int actionBegin, int actionEnd, std::vector<context*>& stack, std::string& out, int indent)
4976  {
4977  int current = actionBegin;
4978 
4979  if (indent)
4980  out.insert(out.size(), indent, ' ');
4981 
4982  while(current < actionEnd)
4983  {
4984  auto& fragment = fragments_[current];
4985  auto& action = actions_[current];
4986  render_fragment(fragment, indent, out);
4987  switch(action.t)
4988  {
4989  case ActionType::Ignore:
4990  // do nothing
4991  break;
4992  case ActionType::Partial:
4993  {
4994  std::string partial_name = tag_name(action);
4995  auto partial_templ = load(partial_name);
4996  int partial_indent = action.pos;
4997  partial_templ.render_internal(0, partial_templ.fragments_.size()-1, stack, out, partial_indent?indent+partial_indent:0);
4998  }
4999  break;
5000  case ActionType::UnescapeTag:
5001  case ActionType::Tag:
5002  {
5003  auto optional_ctx = find_context(tag_name(action), stack);
5004  auto& ctx = optional_ctx.second;
5005  switch(ctx.t())
5006  {
5007  case json::type::Number:
5008  out += json::dump(ctx);
5009  break;
5010  case json::type::String:
5011  if (action.t == ActionType::Tag)
5012  escape(ctx.s, out);
5013  else
5014  out += ctx.s;
5015  break;
5016  default:
5017  throw std::runtime_error("not implemented tag type" + boost::lexical_cast<std::string>((int)ctx.t()));
5018  }
5019  }
5020  break;
5021  case ActionType::ElseBlock:
5022  {
5023  static context nullContext;
5024  auto optional_ctx = find_context(tag_name(action), stack);
5025  if (!optional_ctx.first)
5026  {
5027  stack.emplace_back(&nullContext);
5028  break;
5029  }
5030 
5031  auto& ctx = optional_ctx.second;
5032  switch(ctx.t())
5033  {
5034  case json::type::List:
5035  if (ctx.l && !ctx.l->empty())
5036  current = action.pos;
5037  else
5038  stack.emplace_back(&nullContext);
5039  break;
5040  case json::type::False:
5041  case json::type::Null:
5042  stack.emplace_back(&nullContext);
5043  break;
5044  default:
5045  current = action.pos;
5046  break;
5047  }
5048  break;
5049  }
5050  case ActionType::OpenBlock:
5051  {
5052  auto optional_ctx = find_context(tag_name(action), stack);
5053  if (!optional_ctx.first)
5054  {
5055  current = action.pos;
5056  break;
5057  }
5058 
5059  auto& ctx = optional_ctx.second;
5060  switch(ctx.t())
5061  {
5062  case json::type::List:
5063  if (ctx.l)
5064  for(auto it = ctx.l->begin(); it != ctx.l->end(); ++it)
5065  {
5066  stack.push_back(&*it);
5067  render_internal(current+1, action.pos, stack, out, indent);
5068  stack.pop_back();
5069  }
5070  current = action.pos;
5071  break;
5072  case json::type::Number:
5073  case json::type::String:
5074  case json::type::Object:
5075  case json::type::True:
5076  stack.push_back(&ctx);
5077  break;
5078  case json::type::False:
5079  case json::type::Null:
5080  current = action.pos;
5081  break;
5082  default:
5083  throw std::runtime_error("{{#: not implemented context type: " + boost::lexical_cast<std::string>((int)ctx.t()));
5084  break;
5085  }
5086  break;
5087  }
5088  case ActionType::CloseBlock:
5089  stack.pop_back();
5090  break;
5091  default:
5092  throw std::runtime_error("not implemented " + boost::lexical_cast<std::string>((int)action.t));
5093  }
5094  current++;
5095  }
5096  auto& fragment = fragments_[actionEnd];
5097  render_fragment(fragment, indent, out);
5098  }
5099  void render_fragment(const std::pair<int, int> fragment, int indent, std::string& out)
5100  {
5101  if (indent)
5102  {
5103  for(int i = fragment.first; i < fragment.second; i ++)
5104  {
5105  out += body_[i];
5106  if (body_[i] == '\n' && i+1 != (int)body_.size())
5107  out.insert(out.size(), indent, ' ');
5108  }
5109  }
5110  else
5111  out.insert(out.size(), body_, fragment.first, fragment.second-fragment.first);
5112  }
5113  public:
5114  std::string render()
5115  {
5116  context empty_ctx;
5117  std::vector<context*> stack;
5118  stack.emplace_back(&empty_ctx);
5119 
5120  std::string ret;
5121  render_internal(0, fragments_.size()-1, stack, ret, 0);
5122  return ret;
5123  }
5124  std::string render(context& ctx)
5125  {
5126  std::vector<context*> stack;
5127  stack.emplace_back(&ctx);
5128 
5129  std::string ret;
5130  render_internal(0, fragments_.size()-1, stack, ret, 0);
5131  return ret;
5132  }
5133 
5134  private:
5135 
5136  void parse()
5137  {
5138  std::string tag_open = "{{";
5139  std::string tag_close = "}}";
5140 
5141  std::vector<int> blockPositions;
5142 
5143  size_t current = 0;
5144  while(1)
5145  {
5146  size_t idx = body_.find(tag_open, current);
5147  if (idx == body_.npos)
5148  {
5149  fragments_.emplace_back(current, body_.size());
5150  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::Ignore, 0, 0);
5151  break;
5152  }
5153  fragments_.emplace_back(current, idx);
5154 
5155  idx += tag_open.size();
5156  size_t endIdx = body_.find(tag_close, idx);
5157  if (endIdx == idx)
5158  {
5159  throw invalid_template_exception("empty tag is not allowed");
5160  }
5161  if (endIdx == body_.npos)
5162  {
5163  // error, no matching tag
5164  throw invalid_template_exception("not matched opening tag");
5165  }
5166  current = endIdx + tag_close.size();
5167  switch(body_[idx])
5168  {
5169  case '#':
5170  idx++;
5171  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5172  while(body_[endIdx-1] == ' ') endIdx--;
5173  blockPositions.emplace_back(actions_.size());
5174  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::OpenBlock, idx, endIdx);
5175  break;
5176  case '/':
5177  idx++;
5178  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5179  while(body_[endIdx-1] == ' ') endIdx--;
5180  {
5181  auto& matched = actions_[blockPositions.back()];
5182  if (body_.compare(idx, endIdx-idx,
5183  body_, matched.start, matched.end - matched.start) != 0)
5184  {
5185  throw invalid_template_exception("not matched {{# {{/ pair: " +
5186  body_.substr(matched.start, matched.end - matched.start) + ", " +
5187  body_.substr(idx, endIdx-idx));
5188  }
5189  matched.pos = actions_.size();
5190  }
5191  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::CloseBlock, idx, endIdx, blockPositions.back());
5192  blockPositions.pop_back();
5193  break;
5194  case '^':
5195  idx++;
5196  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5197  while(body_[endIdx-1] == ' ') endIdx--;
5198  blockPositions.emplace_back(actions_.size());
5199  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::ElseBlock, idx, endIdx);
5200  break;
5201  case '!':
5202  // do nothing action
5203  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::Ignore, idx+1, endIdx);
5204  break;
5205  case '>': // partial
5206  idx++;
5207  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5208  while(body_[endIdx-1] == ' ') endIdx--;
5209  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::Partial, idx, endIdx);
5210  break;
5211  case '{':
5212  if (tag_open != "{{" || tag_close != "}}")
5213  throw invalid_template_exception("cannot use triple mustache when delimiter changed");
5214 
5215  idx ++;
5216  if (body_[endIdx+2] != '}')
5217  {
5218  throw invalid_template_exception("{{{: }}} not matched");
5219  }
5220  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5221  while(body_[endIdx-1] == ' ') endIdx--;
5222  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::UnescapeTag, idx, endIdx);
5223  current++;
5224  break;
5225  case '&':
5226  idx ++;
5227  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5228  while(body_[endIdx-1] == ' ') endIdx--;
5229  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::UnescapeTag, idx, endIdx);
5230  break;
5231  case '=':
5232  // tag itself is no-op
5233  idx ++;
5234  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::Ignore, idx, endIdx);
5235  endIdx --;
5236  if (body_[endIdx] != '=')
5237  throw invalid_template_exception("{{=: not matching = tag: "+body_.substr(idx, endIdx-idx));
5238  endIdx --;
5239  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5240  while(body_[endIdx] == ' ') endIdx--;
5241  endIdx++;
5242  {
5243  bool succeeded = false;
5244  for(size_t i = idx; i < endIdx; i++)
5245  {
5246  if (body_[i] == ' ')
5247  {
5248  tag_open = body_.substr(idx, i-idx);
5249  while(body_[i] == ' ') i++;
5250  tag_close = body_.substr(i, endIdx-i);
5251  if (tag_open.empty())
5252  throw invalid_template_exception("{{=: empty open tag");
5253  if (tag_close.empty())
5254  throw invalid_template_exception("{{=: empty close tag");
5255 
5256  if (tag_close.find(" ") != tag_close.npos)
5257  throw invalid_template_exception("{{=: invalid open/close tag: "+tag_open+" " + tag_close);
5258  succeeded = true;
5259  break;
5260  }
5261  }
5262  if (!succeeded)
5263  throw invalid_template_exception("{{=: cannot find space between new open/close tags");
5264  }
5265  break;
5266  default:
5267  // normal tag case;
5268  while(body_[idx] == ' ') idx++;
5269  while(body_[endIdx-1] == ' ') endIdx--;
5270  actions_.emplace_back(ActionType::Tag, idx, endIdx);
5271  break;
5272  }
5273  }
5274 
5275  // removing standalones
5276  for(int i = actions_.size()-2; i >= 0; i --)
5277  {
5278  if (actions_[i].t == ActionType::Tag || actions_[i].t == ActionType::UnescapeTag)
5279  continue;
5280  auto& fragment_before = fragments_[i];
5281  auto& fragment_after = fragments_[i+1];
5282  bool is_last_action = i == (int)actions_.size()-2;
5283  bool all_space_before = true;
5284  int j, k;
5285  for(j = fragment_before.second-1;j >= fragment_before.first;j--)
5286  {
5287  if (body_[j] != ' ')
5288  {
5289  all_space_before = false;
5290  break;
5291  }
5292  }
5293  if (all_space_before && i > 0)
5294  continue;
5295  if (!all_space_before && body_[j] != '\n')
5296  continue;
5297  bool all_space_after = true;
5298  for(k = fragment_after.first; k < (int)body_.size() && k < fragment_after.second; k ++)
5299  {
5300  if (body_[k] != ' ')
5301  {
5302  all_space_after = false;
5303  break;
5304  }
5305  }
5306  if (all_space_after && !is_last_action)
5307  continue;
5308  if (!all_space_after &&
5309  !(
5310  body_[k] == '\n'
5311  ||
5312  (body_[k] == '\r' &&
5313  k + 1 < (int)body_.size() &&
5314  body_[k+1] == '\n')))
5315  continue;
5316  if (actions_[i].t == ActionType::Partial)
5317  {
5318  actions_[i].pos = fragment_before.second - j - 1;
5319  }
5320  fragment_before.second = j+1;
5321  if (!all_space_after)
5322  {
5323  if (body_[k] == '\n')
5324  k++;
5325  else
5326  k += 2;
5327  fragment_after.first = k;
5328  }
5329  }
5330  }
5331 
5332  std::vector<std::pair<int,int>> fragments_;
5333  std::vector<Action> actions_;
5334  std::string body_;
5335  };
5336 
5337  inline template_t compile(const std::string& body)
5338  {
5339  return template_t(body);
5340  }

5344  {
5345  static std::string template_base_directory = "templates";
5346  return template_base_directory;
5347  }

5350  inline std::string default_loader(const std::string& filename)
5351  {
5352  std::string path = detail::get_template_base_directory_ref();
5353  if (!(path.back() == '/' || path.back() == '\\'))
5354  path += '/';
5355  path += filename;
5356  std::ifstream inf(path);
5357  if (!inf)
5358  return {};
5359  return {std::istreambuf_iterator<char>(inf), std::istreambuf_iterator<char>()};
5360  }
5361 
5362  namespace detail
5363  {
5364  inline std::function<std::string (std::string)>& get_loader_ref()
5365  {
5366  static std::function<std::string (std::string)> loader = default_loader;
5367  return loader;
5368  }
5369  }
5370 
5371  inline void set_base(const std::string& path)
5372  {
5373  auto& base = detail::get_template_base_directory_ref();
5374  base = path;
5375  if (base.back() != '\\' &&
5376  base.back() != '/')
5377  {
5378  base += '/';
5379  }
5380  }
5381 
5382  inline void set_loader(std::function<std::string(std::string)> loader)
5383  {
5384  detail::get_loader_ref() = std::move(loader);
5385  }
5386 
5387  inline std::string load_text(const std::string& filename)
5388  {
5389  return detail::get_loader_ref()(filename);
5390  }
5391

5393  {
5394  return compile(detail::get_loader_ref()(filename));
5395  }
5396  }

5460

5557 
5558 namespace crow
5559 {
5560  namespace detail
5561  {
5562  // fast timer queue for fixed tick value.
5563  class dumb_timer_queue
5564  {
5565  public:
5566  using key = std::pair<dumb_timer_queue*, int>;
5567 
5568  void cancel(key& k)
5569  {
5570  auto self = k.first;
5571  k.first = nullptr;
5572  if (!self)
5573  return;
5574 
5575  unsigned int index = (unsigned int)(k.second - self->step_);
5576  if (index < self->dq_.size())
5577  self->dq_[index].second = nullptr;
5578  }
5579 
5580  key add(std::function<void()> f)
5581  {
5582  dq_.emplace_back(std::chrono::steady_clock::now(), std::move(f));
5583  int ret = step_+dq_.size()-1;
5584 
5585  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "timer add inside: " << this << ' ' << ret ;
5586  return {this, ret};
5587  }
5588 
5589  void process()
5590  {
5591  if (!io_service_)
5592  return;
5593 
5594  auto now = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
5595  while(!dq_.empty())
5596  {
5597  auto& x = dq_.front();
5598  if (now - x.first < std::chrono::seconds(tick))
5599  break;
5600  if (x.second)
5601  {
5602  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "timer call: " << this << ' ' << step_;
5603  // we know that timer handlers are very simple currenty; call here
5604  x.second();
5605  }
5606  dq_.pop_front();
5607  step_++;
5608  }
5609  }
5610 
5611  void set_io_service(boost::asio::io_service& io_service)
5612  {
5613  io_service_ = &io_service;
5614  }
5615 
5616  dumb_timer_queue() noexcept
5617  {
5618  }
5619 
5620  private:
5621 
5622  int tick{5};
5623  boost::asio::io_service* io_service_{};

5685  constexpr unsigned find_closing_tag(const_str s, unsigned p)
5686  {

5689 
5690  constexpr bool is_valid(const_str s, unsigned i = 0, int f = 0)
5691  {
5692  return
5693  i == s.size()
5694  ? f == 0 :
5695  f < 0 || f >= 2
5696  ? false :
5697  s[i] == '<'
5698  ? is_valid(s, i+1, f+1) :
5699  s[i] == '>'
5700  ? is_valid(s, i+1, f-1) :
5701  is_valid(s, i+1, f);
5702  }
5703 
5704  constexpr bool is_equ_p(const char* a, const char* b, unsigned n)
5705  {
5706  return
5707  *a == 0 && *b == 0 && n == 0
5708  ? true :
5709  (*a == 0 || *b == 0)
5710  ? false :
5711  n == 0
5712  ? true :
5713  *a != *b
5714  ? false :
5715  is_equ_p(a+1, b+1, n-1);
5716  }
5717 
5718  constexpr bool is_equ_n(const_str a, unsigned ai, const_str b, unsigned bi, unsigned n)
5719  {
5720  return
5721  ai + n > a.size() || bi + n > b.size()
5722  ? false :
5723  n == 0
5724  ? true :
5725  a[ai] != b[bi]
5726  ? false :
5727  is_equ_n(a,ai+1,b,bi+1,n-1);
5728  }
5729 
5730  constexpr bool is_int(const_str s, unsigned i)
5731  {
5732  return is_equ_n(s, i, "<int>", 0, 5);
5733  }
5734 
5735  constexpr bool is_uint(const_str s, unsigned i)
5736  {
5737  return is_equ_n(s, i, "<uint>", 0, 6);
5738  }
5739 
5740  constexpr bool is_float(const_str s, unsigned i)
5741  {
5742  return is_equ_n(s, i, "<float>", 0, 7) ||
5743  is_equ_n(s, i, "<double>", 0, 8);
5744  }
5745 
5746  constexpr bool is_str(const_str s, unsigned i)
5747  {
5748  return is_equ_n(s, i, "<str>", 0, 5) ||
5749  is_equ_n(s, i, "<string>", 0, 8);
5750  }
5751 
5752  constexpr bool is_path(const_str s, unsigned i)
5753  {
5754  return is_equ_n(s, i, "<path>", 0, 6);
5755  }
5756 #endif
5757  template <typename T>
5758  struct parameter_tag
5759  {
5760  static const int value = 0;
5761  };
5762 #define CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(t, i) \
5763 template <> \
5764 struct parameter_tag<t> \
5765 { \
5766  static const int value = i; \
5767 }
5768  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(int, 1);
5769  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(char, 1);
5770  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(short, 1);
5771  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(long, 1);
5772  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(long long, 1);
5773  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(unsigned int, 2);
5774  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(unsigned char, 2);
5775  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(unsigned short, 2);
5776  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(unsigned long, 2);
5777  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(unsigned long long, 2);
5778  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(double, 3);
5779  CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG(std::string, 4);
5780 #undef CROW_INTERNAL_PARAMETER_TAG
5781  template <typename ... Args>
5782  struct compute_parameter_tag_from_args_list;
5783 
5784  template <>
5785  struct compute_parameter_tag_from_args_list<>
5786  {
5787  static const int value = 0;
5788  };
5789 
5790  template <typename Arg, typename ... Args>
5791  struct compute_parameter_tag_from_args_list<Arg, Args...>
5792  {
5793  static const int sub_value =
5794  compute_parameter_tag_from_args_list<Args...>::value;
5795  static const int value =
5796  parameter_tag<typename std::decay<Arg>::type>::value
5797  ? sub_value* 6 + parameter_tag<typename std::decay<Arg>::type>::value
5798  : sub_value;
5799  };
5800 
5801  static inline bool is_parameter_tag_compatible(uint64_t a, uint64_t b)
5802  {
5803  if (a == 0)
5804  return b == 0;
5805  if (b == 0)
5806  return a == 0;
5807  int sa = a%6;
5808  int sb = a%6;
5809  if (sa == 5) sa = 4;
5810  if (sb == 5) sb = 4;
5811  if (sa != sb)
5812  return false;
5813  return is_parameter_tag_compatible(a/6, b/6);
5814  }
5815 
5816  static inline unsigned find_closing_tag_runtime(const char* s, unsigned p)
5817  {
5818  return
5819  s[p] == 0
5820  ? throw std::runtime_error("unmatched tag <") :
5821  s[p] == '>'
5822  ? p : find_closing_tag_runtime(s, p + 1);
5823  }
5824 
5825  static inline uint64_t get_parameter_tag_runtime(const char* s, unsigned p = 0)
5826  {
5827  return
5828  s[p] == 0
5829  ? 0 :
5830  s[p] == '<' ? (
5831  std::strncmp(s+p, "<int>", 5) == 0
5832  ? get_parameter_tag_runtime(s, find_closing_tag_runtime(s, p)) * 6 + 1 :
5833  std::strncmp(s+p, "<uint>", 6) == 0
5834  ? get_parameter_tag_runtime(s, find_closing_tag_runtime(s, p)) * 6 + 2 :
5835  (std::strncmp(s+p, "<float>", 7) == 0 ||
5836  std::strncmp(s+p, "<double>", 8) == 0)
5837  ? get_parameter_tag_runtime(s, find_closing_tag_runtime(s, p)) * 6 + 3 :
5838  (std::strncmp(s+p, "<str>", 5) == 0 ||
5839  std::strncmp(s+p, "<string>", 8) == 0)
5840  ? get_parameter_tag_runtime(s, find_closing_tag_runtime(s, p)) * 6 + 4 :
5841  std::strncmp(s+p, "<path>", 6) == 0
5842  ? get_parameter_tag_runtime(s, find_closing_tag_runtime(s, p)) * 6 + 5 :
5843  throw std::runtime_error("invalid parameter type")
5844  ) :
5845  get_parameter_tag_runtime(s, p+1);
5846  }
5847 #ifndef CROW_MSVC_WORKAROUND
5848  constexpr uint64_t get_parameter_tag(const_str s, unsigned p = 0)
5849  {
5850  return
5851  p == s.size()
5852  ? 0 :
5853  s[p] == '<' ? (
5854  is_int(s, p)
5855  ? get_parameter_tag(s, find_closing_tag(s, p)) * 6 + 1 :
5856  is_uint(s, p)
5857  ? get_parameter_tag(s, find_closing_tag(s, p)) * 6 + 2 :
5858  is_float(s, p)
5859  ? get_parameter_tag(s, find_closing_tag(s, p)) * 6 + 3 :
5860  is_str(s, p)
5861  ? get_parameter_tag(s, find_closing_tag(s, p)) * 6 + 4 :
5862  is_path(s, p)
5863  ? get_parameter_tag(s, find_closing_tag(s, p)) * 6 + 5 :
5864  throw std::runtime_error("invalid parameter type")
5865  ) :
5866  get_parameter_tag(s, p+1);
5867  }
5868 #endif

6137  inline static std::string base64encode(const char* data, size_t size, const char* key = "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789+/")
6138  {
6139  std::string ret;
6140  ret.resize((size+2) / 3 * 4);
6141  auto it = ret.begin();
6142  while(size >= 3)
6143  {
6144  *it++ = key[(((unsigned char)*data)&0xFC)>>2];
6145  unsigned char h = (((unsigned char)*data++) & 0x03) << 4;
6146  *it++ = key[h|((((unsigned char)*data)&0xF0)>>4)];
6147  h = (((unsigned char)*data++) & 0x0F) << 2;
6148  *it++ = key[h|((((unsigned char)*data)&0xC0)>>6)];
6149  *it++ = key[((unsigned char)*data++)&0x3F];
6150 
6151  size -= 3;
6152  }
6153  if (size == 1)
6154  {
6155  *it++ = key[(((unsigned char)*data)&0xFC)>>2];
6156  unsigned char h = (((unsigned char)*data++) & 0x03) << 4;
6157  *it++ = key[h];
6158  *it++ = '=';
6159  *it++ = '=';
6160  }
6161  else if (size == 2)
6162  {
6163  *it++ = key[(((unsigned char)*data)&0xFC)>>2];
6164  unsigned char h = (((unsigned char)*data++) & 0x03) << 4;
6165  *it++ = key[h|((((unsigned char)*data)&0xF0)>>4)];
6166  h = (((unsigned char)*data++) & 0x0F) << 2;
6167  *it++ = key[h];
6168  *it++ = '=';
6169  }
6170  return ret;
6171  }
6172 
6173  inline static std::string base64encode_urlsafe(const char* data, size_t size)
6174  {
6175  return base64encode(data, size, "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZabcdefghijklmnopqrstuvwxyz0123456789-_");
6176  }

6307 #ifndef CROW_MSVC_WORKAROUND
6308 constexpr crow::HTTPMethod operator "" _method(const char* str, size_t /*len*/)
6309 {
6310  return
6311  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "GET", 3) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Get :
6312  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "DELETE", 6) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Delete :
6313  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "HEAD", 4) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Head :
6314  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "POST", 4) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Post :
6315  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "PUT", 3) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Put :
6316  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "OPTIONS", 7) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Options :
6317  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "CONNECT", 7) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Connect :
6318  crow::black_magic::is_equ_p(str, "TRACE", 5) ? crow::HTTPMethod::Trace :
6319  throw std::runtime_error("invalid http method");
6320 }

6436  template <typename Adaptor>
6437  class Connection : public connection
6438  {
6439  public:
6440  Connection(const crow::request& req, Adaptor&& adaptor,
6441  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&)> open_handler,
6442  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&, const std::string&, bool)> message_handler,
6443  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&, const std::string&)> close_handler,
6444  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&)> error_handler)
6445  : adaptor_(std::move(adaptor)), open_handler_(std::move(open_handler)), message_handler_(std::move(message_handler)), close_handler_(std::move(close_handler)), error_handler_(std::move(error_handler))
6446  {
6447  if (!boost::iequals(req.get_header_value("upgrade"), "websocket"))
6448  {
6449  adaptor.close();
6450  delete this;
6451  return;
6452  }
6453  // Sec-WebSocket-Key: dGhlIHNhbXBsZSBub25jZQ==
6454  // Sec-WebSocket-Version: 13
6455  std::string magic = req.get_header_value("Sec-WebSocket-Key") + "258EAFA5-E914-47DA-95CA-C5AB0DC85B11";
6456  sha1::SHA1 s;
6457  s.processBytes(magic.data(), magic.size());
6458  uint8_t digest[20];
6459  s.getDigestBytes(digest);
6460  start(crow::utility::base64encode((char*)digest, 20));
6461  }

6463  template<typename CompletionHandler>

6474 
6475  void send_pong(const std::string& msg)
6476  {
6477  dispatch([this, msg]{
6478  char buf[3] = "\x8A\x00";
6479  buf[1] += msg.size();
6480  write_buffers_.emplace_back(buf, buf+2);
6481  write_buffers_.emplace_back(msg);
6482  do_write();
6483  });
6484  }
6485 
6486  void send_binary(const std::string& msg) override
6487  {
6488  dispatch([this, msg]{
6489  auto header = build_header(2, msg.size());
6490  write_buffers_.emplace_back(std::move(header));
6491  write_buffers_.emplace_back(msg);
6492  do_write();
6493  });
6494  }
6495 
6496  void send_text(const std::string& msg) override
6497  {
6498  dispatch([this, msg]{
6499  auto header = build_header(1, msg.size());
6500  write_buffers_.emplace_back(std::move(header));
6501  write_buffers_.emplace_back(msg);
6502  do_write();
6503  });
6504  }
6505 
6506  void close(const std::string& msg) override
6507  {
6508  dispatch([this, msg]{
6509  has_sent_close_ = true;
6510  if (has_recv_close_ && !is_close_handler_called_)
6511  {
6512  is_close_handler_called_ = true;
6513  if (close_handler_)
6514  close_handler_(*this, msg);
6515  }
6516  auto header = build_header(0x8, msg.size());
6517  write_buffers_.emplace_back(std::move(header));
6518  write_buffers_.emplace_back(msg);
6519  do_write();
6520  });
6521  }
6522 
6523  protected:
6524 
6525  std::string build_header(int opcode, size_t size)
6526  {
6527  char buf[2+8] = "\x80\x00";
6528  buf[0] += opcode;
6529  if (size < 126)
6530  {
6531  buf[1] += size;
6532  return {buf, buf+2};
6533  }
6534  else if (size < 0x10000)
6535  {
6536  buf[1] += 126;
6537  *(uint16_t*)(buf+2) = htons((uint16_t)size);
6538  return {buf, buf+4};
6539  }
6540  else
6541  {
6542  buf[1] += 127;
6543  *(uint64_t*)(buf+2) = ((1==htonl(1)) ? (uint64_t)size : ((uint64_t)htonl((size) & 0xFFFFFFFF) << 32) | htonl((size) >> 32));
6544  return {buf, buf+10};
6545  }
6546  }
6547 
6548  void start(std::string&& hello)
6549  {
6550  static std::string header = "HTTP/1.1 101 Switching Protocols\r\n"
6551  "Upgrade: websocket\r\n"
6552  "Connection: Upgrade\r\n"
6553  "Sec-WebSocket-Accept: ";
6554  static std::string crlf = "\r\n";
6555  write_buffers_.emplace_back(header);
6556  write_buffers_.emplace_back(std::move(hello));
6557  write_buffers_.emplace_back(crlf);
6558  write_buffers_.emplace_back(crlf);
6559  do_write();
6560  if (open_handler_)
6561  open_handler_(*this);
6562  do_read();
6563  }
6564 
6565  void do_read()
6566  {
6567  is_reading = true;
6568  switch(state_)
6569  {
6570  case WebSocketReadState::MiniHeader:
6571  {
6572  //boost::asio::async_read(adaptor_.socket(), boost::asio::buffer(&mini_header_, 1),
6573  adaptor_.socket().async_read_some(boost::asio::buffer(&mini_header_, 2),
6574  [this](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t bytes_transferred)
6575  {
6576  is_reading = false;
6577  mini_header_ = htons(mini_header_);
6578 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_DEBUG
6579 
6580  if (!ec && bytes_transferred != 2)
6581  {
6582  throw std::runtime_error("WebSocket:MiniHeader:async_read fail:asio bug?");
6583  }
6584 #endif
6585 
6586  if (!ec && ((mini_header_ & 0x80) == 0x80))
6587  {
6588  if ((mini_header_ & 0x7f) == 127)
6589  {
6590  state_ = WebSocketReadState::Len64;
6591  }
6592  else if ((mini_header_ & 0x7f) == 126)
6593  {
6594  state_ = WebSocketReadState::Len16;
6595  }
6596  else
6597  {
6598  remaining_length_ = mini_header_ & 0x7f;
6599  state_ = WebSocketReadState::Mask;
6600  }
6601  do_read();
6602  }
6603  else
6604  {
6605  close_connection_ = true;
6606  adaptor_.close();
6607  if (error_handler_)
6608  error_handler_(*this);
6609  check_destroy();
6610  }
6611  });
6612  }
6613  break;
6614  case WebSocketReadState::Len16:
6615  {
6616  remaining_length_ = 0;
6617  boost::asio::async_read(adaptor_.socket(), boost::asio::buffer(&remaining_length_, 2),
6618  [this](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t bytes_transferred)
6619  {
6620  is_reading = false;
6621  remaining_length_ = ntohs(*(uint16_t*)&remaining_length_);
6622 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_DEBUG
6623  if (!ec && bytes_transferred != 2)
6624  {
6625  throw std::runtime_error("WebSocket:Len16:async_read fail:asio bug?");
6626  }
6627 #endif
6628 
6629  if (!ec)
6630  {
6631  state_ = WebSocketReadState::Mask;
6632  do_read();
6633  }
6634  else
6635  {
6636  close_connection_ = true;
6637  adaptor_.close();
6638  if (error_handler_)
6639  error_handler_(*this);
6640  check_destroy();
6641  }
6642  });
6643  }
6644  break;
6645  case WebSocketReadState::Len64:
6646  {
6647  boost::asio::async_read(adaptor_.socket(), boost::asio::buffer(&remaining_length_, 8),
6648  [this](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t bytes_transferred)
6649  {
6650  is_reading = false;
6651  remaining_length_ = ((1==ntohl(1)) ? (remaining_length_) : ((uint64_t)ntohl((remaining_length_) & 0xFFFFFFFF) << 32) | ntohl((remaining_length_) >> 32));
6652 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_DEBUG
6653  if (!ec && bytes_transferred != 8)
6654  {
6655  throw std::runtime_error("WebSocket:Len16:async_read fail:asio bug?");
6656  }
6657 #endif
6658 
6659  if (!ec)
6660  {
6661  state_ = WebSocketReadState::Mask;
6662  do_read();
6663  }
6664  else
6665  {
6666  close_connection_ = true;
6667  adaptor_.close();
6668  if (error_handler_)
6669  error_handler_(*this);
6670  check_destroy();
6671  }
6672  });
6673  }
6674  break;
6675  case WebSocketReadState::Mask:
6676  boost::asio::async_read(adaptor_.socket(), boost::asio::buffer((char*)&mask_, 4),
6677  [this](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t bytes_transferred)
6678  {
6679  is_reading = false;
6680 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_DEBUG
6681  if (!ec && bytes_transferred != 4)
6682  {
6683  throw std::runtime_error("WebSocket:Mask:async_read fail:asio bug?");
6684  }
6685 #endif
6686 
6687  if (!ec)
6688  {
6689  state_ = WebSocketReadState::Payload;
6690  do_read();
6691  }
6692  else
6693  {
6694  close_connection_ = true;
6695  if (error_handler_)
6696  error_handler_(*this);
6697  adaptor_.close();
6698  }
6699  });
6700  break;
6701  case WebSocketReadState::Payload:
6702  {
6703  size_t to_read = buffer_.size();
6704  if (remaining_length_ < to_read)
6705  to_read = remaining_length_;
6706  adaptor_.socket().async_read_some( boost::asio::buffer(buffer_, to_read),
6707  [this](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t bytes_transferred)
6708  {
6709  is_reading = false;
6710 
6711  if (!ec)
6712  {
6713  fragment_.insert(fragment_.end(), buffer_.begin(), buffer_.begin() + bytes_transferred);
6714  remaining_length_ -= bytes_transferred;
6715  if (remaining_length_ == 0)
6716  {
6717  handle_fragment();
6718  state_ = WebSocketReadState::MiniHeader;
6719  do_read();
6720  }
6721  }
6722  else
6723  {
6724  close_connection_ = true;
6725  if (error_handler_)
6726  error_handler_(*this);
6727  adaptor_.close();
6728  }
6729  });
6730  }
6731  break;
6732  }
6733  }
6734 
6735  bool is_FIN()
6736  {
6737  return mini_header_ & 0x8000;
6738  }
6739 
6740  int opcode()
6741  {
6742  return (mini_header_ & 0x0f00) >> 8;
6743  }
6744 
6745  void handle_fragment()
6746  {
6747  for(decltype(fragment_.length()) i = 0; i < fragment_.length(); i ++)
6748  {
6749  fragment_[i] ^= ((char*)&mask_)[i%4];
6750  }
6751  switch(opcode())
6752  {
6753  case 0: // Continuation
6754  {
6755  message_ += fragment_;
6756  if (is_FIN())
6757  {
6758  if (message_handler_)
6759  message_handler_(*this, message_, is_binary_);
6760  message_.clear();
6761  }
6762  }
6763  case 1: // Text
6764  {
6765  is_binary_ = false;
6766  message_ += fragment_;
6767  if (is_FIN())
6768  {
6769  if (message_handler_)
6770  message_handler_(*this, message_, is_binary_);
6771  message_.clear();
6772  }
6773  }
6774  break;
6775  case 2: // Binary
6776  {
6777  is_binary_ = true;
6778  message_ += fragment_;
6779  if (is_FIN())
6780  {
6781  if (message_handler_)
6782  message_handler_(*this, message_, is_binary_);
6783  message_.clear();
6784  }
6785  }
6786  break;
6787  case 0x8: // Close
6788  {
6789  has_recv_close_ = true;
6790  if (!has_sent_close_)
6791  {
6792  close(fragment_);
6793  }
6794  else
6795  {
6796  adaptor_.close();
6797  close_connection_ = true;
6798  if (!is_close_handler_called_)
6799  {
6800  if (close_handler_)
6801  close_handler_(*this, fragment_);
6802  is_close_handler_called_ = true;
6803  }
6804  check_destroy();
6805  }
6806  }
6807  break;
6808  case 0x9: // Ping
6809  {
6810  send_pong(fragment_);
6811  }
6812  break;
6813  case 0xA: // Pong
6814  {
6815  pong_received_ = true;
6816  }
6817  break;
6818  }
6819 
6820  fragment_.clear();
6821  }
6822 
6823  void do_write()
6824  {
6825  if (sending_buffers_.empty())
6826  {
6827  sending_buffers_.swap(write_buffers_);
6828  std::vector<boost::asio::const_buffer> buffers;
6829  buffers.reserve(sending_buffers_.size());
6830  for(auto& s:sending_buffers_)
6831  {
6832  buffers.emplace_back(boost::asio::buffer(s));
6833  }
6834  boost::asio::async_write(adaptor_.socket(), buffers,
6835  [&](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t /*bytes_transferred*/)
6836  {
6837  sending_buffers_.clear();
6838  if (!ec && !close_connection_)
6839  {
6840  if (!write_buffers_.empty())
6841  do_write();
6842  if (has_sent_close_)
6843  close_connection_ = true;
6844  }
6845  else
6846  {
6847  close_connection_ = true;
6848  check_destroy();
6849  }
6850  });
6851  }
6852  }
6853 
6854  void check_destroy()
6855  {
6856  //if (has_sent_close_ && has_recv_close_)
6857  if (!is_close_handler_called_)
6858  if (close_handler_)
6859  close_handler_(*this, "uncleanly");
6860  if (sending_buffers_.empty() && !is_reading)
6861  delete this;
6862  }
6863  private:
6864  Adaptor adaptor_;
6865 
6866  std::vector<std::string> sending_buffers_;
6867  std::vector<std::string> write_buffers_;
6868 
6869  boost::array<char, 4096> buffer_;
6870  bool is_binary_;
6871  std::string message_;
6872  std::string fragment_;
6873  WebSocketReadState state_{WebSocketReadState::MiniHeader};
6874  uint64_t remaining_length_{0};
6875  bool close_connection_{false};
6876  bool is_reading{false};
6877  uint32_t mask_;
6878  uint16_t mini_header_;
6879  bool has_sent_close_{false};
6880  bool has_recv_close_{false};
6881  bool error_occured_{false};
6882  bool pong_received_{false};
6883  bool is_close_handler_called_{false};
6884 
6885  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&)> open_handler_;
6886  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&, const std::string&, bool)> message_handler_;
6887  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&, const std::string&)> close_handler_;
6888  std::function<void(crow::websocket::connection&)> error_handler_;
6889  };
6890  }
6891 }

6898 #include <unordered_map>
6899 #include <boost/algorithm/string.hpp>
6900 #include <boost/tokenizer.hpp>
6901 #include <algorithm>

6907 
6908 namespace crow
6909 {
6910  template <typename Handler>
6911  struct HTTPParser : public http_parser
6912  {
6913  static int on_message_begin(http_parser* self_)
6914  {
6915  HTTPParser* self = static_cast<HTTPParser*>(self_);
6916  self->clear();
6917  return 0;
6918  }
6919  static int on_url(http_parser* self_, const char* at, size_t length)
6920  {
6921  HTTPParser* self = static_cast<HTTPParser*>(self_);
6922  self->raw_url.insert(self->raw_url.end(), at, at+length);
6923  return 0;
6924  }
6925  static int on_header_field(http_parser* self_, const char* at, size_t length)
6926  {
6927  HTTPParser* self = static_cast<HTTPParser*>(self_);
6928  switch (self->header_building_state)
6929  {
6930  case 0:
6931  if (!self->header_value.empty())
6932  {
6933  self->headers.emplace(std::move(self->header_field), std::move(self->header_value));
6934  }
6935  self->header_field.assign(at, at+length);
6936  self->header_building_state = 1;
6937  break;
6938  case 1:
6939  self->header_field.insert(self->header_field.end(), at, at+length);
6940  break;
6941  }
6942  return 0;
6943  }
6944  static int on_header_value(http_parser* self_, const char* at, size_t length)
6945  {
6946  HTTPParser* self = static_cast<HTTPParser*>(self_);
6947  switch (self->header_building_state)
6948  {
6949  case 0:
6950  self->header_value.insert(self->header_value.end(), at, at+length);
6951  break;
6952  case 1:
6953  self->header_building_state = 0;
6954  self->header_value.assign(at, at+length);
6955  break;
6956  }
6957  return 0;
6958  }
6959  static int on_headers_complete(http_parser* self_)
6960  {
6961  HTTPParser* self = static_cast<HTTPParser*>(self_);
6962  if (!self->header_field.empty())
6963  {
6964  self->headers.emplace(std::move(self->header_field), std::move(self->header_value));
6965  }
6966  self->process_header();
6967  return 0;
6968  }
6969  static int on_body(http_parser* self_, const char* at, size_t length)
6970  {
6971  HTTPParser* self = static_cast<HTTPParser*>(self_);
6972  self->body.insert(self->body.end(), at, at+length);
6973  return 0;
6974  }
6975  static int on_message_complete(http_parser* self_)
6976  {
6977  HTTPParser* self = static_cast<HTTPParser*>(self_);
6978 
6979  // url params
6980  self->url = self->raw_url.substr(0, self->raw_url.find("?"));
6981  self->url_params = query_string(self->raw_url);
6982 
6983  self->process_message();
6984  return 0;
6985  }
6986  HTTPParser(Handler* handler) :
6987  handler_(handler)
6988  {
6989  http_parser_init(this, HTTP_REQUEST);
6990  }
6991 
6992  // return false on error
6993  bool feed(const char* buffer, int length)
6994  {
6995  const static http_parser_settings settings_{
6996  on_message_begin,
6997  on_url,
6998  nullptr,
6999  on_header_field,
7000  on_header_value,
7001  on_headers_complete,
7002  on_body,
7003  on_message_complete,
7004  };
7005 
7006  int nparsed = http_parser_execute(this, &settings_, buffer, length);
7007  return nparsed == length;
7008  }
7009 
7010  bool done()
7011  {
7012  return feed(nullptr, 0);
7013  }
7014 
7015  void clear()
7016  {
7017  url.clear();
7018  raw_url.clear();
7019  header_building_state = 0;
7020  header_field.clear();
7021  header_value.clear();
7022  headers.clear();
7023  url_params.clear();
7024  body.clear();
7025  }
7026 
7027  void process_header()
7028  {
7029  handler_->handle_header();
7030  }
7031 
7032  void process_message()
7033  {
7034  handler_->handle();
7035  }
7036 
7037  request to_request() const
7038  {
7039  return request{(HTTPMethod)method, std::move(raw_url), std::move(url), std::move(url_params), std::move(headers), std::move(body)};
7040  }
7041 
7042  bool is_upgrade() const
7043  {
7044  return upgrade;
7045  }
7046 
7047  bool check_version(int major, int minor) const
7048  {
7049  return http_major == major && http_minor == minor;
7050  }
7051 
7052  std::string raw_url;
7053  std::string url;
7054 
7055  int header_building_state = 0;
7056  std::string header_field;
7057  std::string header_value;
7058  ci_map headers;
7059  query_string url_params;
7060  std::string body;
7061 
7062  Handler* handler_;
7063  };
7064 }

7079 namespace crow
7080 {
7081  template <typename Adaptor, typename Handler, typename ... Middlewares>
7082  class Connection;
7083  struct response
7084  {
7085  template <typename Adaptor, typename Handler, typename ... Middlewares>
7086  friend class crow::Connection;
7087 
7088  int code{200};
7089  std::string body;
7090  json::wvalue json_value;
7091 
7092  // `headers' stores HTTP headers.
7093  ci_map headers;
7094 
7095  void set_header(std::string key, std::string value)
7096  {
7097  headers.erase(key);
7098  headers.emplace(std::move(key), std::move(value));
7099  }
7100  void add_header(std::string key, std::string value)
7101  {
7102  headers.emplace(std::move(key), std::move(value));
7103  }
7104 
7105  const std::string& get_header_value(const std::string& key)
7106  {
7107  return crow::get_header_value(headers, key);
7108  }
7109 
7110 
7111  response() {}
7112  explicit response(int code) : code(code) {}
7113  response(std::string body) : body(std::move(body)) {}
7114  response(json::wvalue&& json_value) : json_value(std::move(json_value))
7115  {
7116  json_mode();
7117  }
7118  response(int code, std::string body) : code(code), body(std::move(body)) {}
7119  response(const json::wvalue& json_value) : body(json::dump(json_value))
7120  {
7121  json_mode();
7122  }
7123  response(int code, const json::wvalue& json_value) : code(code), body(json::dump(json_value))
7124  {
7125  json_mode();
7126  }
7127 
7128  response(response&& r)
7129  {
7130  *this = std::move(r);
7131  }
7132 
7133  response& operator = (const response& r) = delete;
7134 
7135  response& operator = (response&& r) noexcept
7136  {
7137  body = std::move(r.body);
7138  json_value = std::move(r.json_value);
7139  code = r.code;
7140  headers = std::move(r.headers);
7141  completed_ = r.completed_;
7142  return *this;
7143  }
7144 
7145  bool is_completed() const noexcept
7146  {
7147  return completed_;
7148  }
7149 
7150  void clear()
7151  {
7152  body.clear();
7153  json_value.clear();
7154  code = 200;
7155  headers.clear();
7156  completed_ = false;
7157  }
7158 
7159  void write(const std::string& body_part)
7160  {
7161  body += body_part;
7162  }
7163 
7164  void end()
7165  {
7166  if (!completed_)
7167  {
7168  completed_ = true;
7169 
7170  if (complete_request_handler_)
7171  {
7172  complete_request_handler_();
7173  }
7174  }
7175  }
7176 
7177  void end(const std::string& body_part)
7178  {
7179  body += body_part;
7180  end();
7181  }
7182 
7183  bool is_alive()
7184  {
7185  return is_alive_helper_ && is_alive_helper_();
7186  }
7187 
7188  private:
7189  bool completed_{};
7190  std::function<void()> complete_request_handler_;
7191  std::function<bool()> is_alive_helper_;
7192 
7193  //In case of a JSON object, set the Content-Type header
7194  void json_mode()
7195  {
7196  set_header("Content-Type", "application/json");
7197  }
7198  };
7199 }

7203 #pragma once
7204 #include <boost/algorithm/string/trim.hpp>
7205 
7206 
7207 
7208 
7209 
7210 namespace crow
7211 {
7212  // Any middleware requires following 3 members:
7213 
7214  // struct context;
7215  // storing data for the middleware; can be read from another middleware or handlers
7216 
7217  // before_handle
7218  // called before handling the request.
7219  // if res.end() is called, the operation is halted.
7220  // (still call after_handle of this middleware)
7221  // 2 signatures:
7222  // void before_handle(request& req, response& res, context& ctx)
7223  // if you only need to access this middlewares context.
7224  // template <typename AllContext>
7225  // void before_handle(request& req, response& res, context& ctx, AllContext& all_ctx)
7226  // you can access another middlewares' context by calling `all_ctx.template get<MW>()'
7227  // ctx == all_ctx.template get<CurrentMiddleware>()
7228 
7229  // after_handle
7230  // called after handling the request.
7231  // void after_handle(request& req, response& res, context& ctx)
7232  // template <typename AllContext>
7233  // void after_handle(request& req, response& res, context& ctx, AllContext& all_ctx)
7234 
7235  struct CookieParser
7236  {
7237  struct context
7238  {
7239  std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string> jar;
7240  std::unordered_map<std::string, std::string> cookies_to_add;
7241 
7242  std::string get_cookie(const std::string& key)
7243  {
7244  if (jar.count(key))
7245  return jar[key];
7246  return {};
7247  }
7248 
7249  void set_cookie(const std::string& key, const std::string& value)
7250  {
7251  cookies_to_add.emplace(key, value);
7252  }
7253  };
7254 
7255  void before_handle(request& req, response& res, context& ctx)
7256  {
7257  int count = req.headers.count("Cookie");
7258  if (!count)
7259  return;
7260  if (count > 1)
7261  {
7262  res.code = 400;
7263  res.end();
7264  return;
7265  }
7266  std::string cookies = req.get_header_value("Cookie");
7267  size_t pos = 0;
7268  while(pos < cookies.size())
7269  {
7270  size_t pos_equal = cookies.find('=', pos);
7271  if (pos_equal == cookies.npos)
7272  break;
7273  std::string name = cookies.substr(pos, pos_equal-pos);
7274  boost::trim(name);
7275  pos = pos_equal+1;
7276  while(pos < cookies.size() && cookies[pos] == ' ') pos++;
7277  if (pos == cookies.size())
7278  break;
7279 
7280  std::string value;
7281 
7282  if (cookies[pos] == '"')
7283  {
7284  int dquote_meet_count = 0;
7285  pos ++;
7286  size_t pos_dquote = pos-1;
7287  do
7288  {
7289  pos_dquote = cookies.find('"', pos_dquote+1);
7290  dquote_meet_count ++;
7291  } while(pos_dquote < cookies.size() && cookies[pos_dquote-1] == '\\');
7292  if (pos_dquote == cookies.npos)
7293  break;
7294 
7295  if (dquote_meet_count == 1)
7296  value = cookies.substr(pos, pos_dquote - pos);
7297  else
7298  {
7299  value.clear();
7300  value.reserve(pos_dquote-pos);
7301  for(size_t p = pos; p < pos_dquote; p++)
7302  {
7303  // FIXME minimal escaping
7304  if (cookies[p] == '\\' && p + 1 < pos_dquote)
7305  {
7306  p++;
7307  if (cookies[p] == '\\' || cookies[p] == '"')
7308  value += cookies[p];
7309  else
7310  {
7311  value += '\\';
7312  value += cookies[p];
7313  }
7314  }
7315  else
7316  value += cookies[p];
7317  }
7318  }
7319 
7320  ctx.jar.emplace(std::move(name), std::move(value));
7321  pos = cookies.find(";", pos_dquote+1);
7322  if (pos == cookies.npos)
7323  break;
7324  pos++;
7325  while(pos < cookies.size() && cookies[pos] == ' ') pos++;
7326  if (pos == cookies.size())
7327  break;
7328  }
7329  else
7330  {
7331  size_t pos_semicolon = cookies.find(';', pos);
7332  value = cookies.substr(pos, pos_semicolon - pos);
7333  boost::trim(value);
7334  ctx.jar.emplace(std::move(name), std::move(value));
7335  pos = pos_semicolon;
7336  if (pos == cookies.npos)
7337  break;
7338  pos ++;
7339  while(pos < cookies.size() && cookies[pos] == ' ') pos++;
7340  if (pos == cookies.size())
7341  break;
7342  }
7343  }
7344  }
7345 
7346  void after_handle(request& /*req*/, response& res, context& ctx)
7347  {
7348  for(auto& cookie:ctx.cookies_to_add)
7349  {
7350  res.add_header("Set-Cookie", cookie.first + "=" + cookie.second);
7351  }
7352  }
7353  };
7354 
7355  /*
7356  App<CookieParser, AnotherJarMW> app;
7357  A B C
7358  A::context
7359  int aa;
7360 
7361  ctx1 : public A::context
7362  ctx2 : public ctx1, public B::context
7363  ctx3 : public ctx2, public C::context
7364 
7365  C depends on A
7366 
7367  C::handle
7368  context.aaa
7369 
7370  App::context : private CookieParser::contetx, ...
7371  {
7372  jar
7373 
7374  }
7375 
7376  SimpleApp
7377  */
7378 }

7485  template <typename F, int NInt, int NUint, int NDouble, int NString, typename ... Args1, typename ... Args2>
7486  struct call<F, NInt, NUint, NDouble, NString, black_magic::S<int64_t, Args1...>, black_magic::S<Args2...>>
7487  {
7488  void operator()(F cparams)
7489  {
7490  using pushed = typename black_magic::S<Args2...>::template push_back<call_pair<int64_t, NInt>>;
7491  call<F, NInt+1, NUint, NDouble, NString,
7492  black_magic::S<Args1...>, pushed>()(cparams);
7493  }
7494  };

7498  {

7500  {

7502  call<F, NInt, NUint+1, NDouble, NString,

7504  }
7505  };

7509  {

7542  template <typename Func, typename ... ArgsWrapped>
7543  struct Wrapped
7544  {
7545  template <typename ... Args>
7546  void set(Func f, typename std::enable_if<
7547  !std::is_same<typename std::tuple_element<0, std::tuple<Args..., void>>::type, const request&>::value
7548  , int>::type = 0)
7549  {
7550  handler_ = (
7551 #ifdef CROW_CAN_USE_CPP14
7552  [f = std::move(f)]
7553 #else
7554  [f]
7555 #endif
7556  (const request&, response& res, Args... args){
7557  res = response(f(args...));
7558  res.end();
7559  });
7560  }
7561 
7562  template <typename Req, typename ... Args>
7563  struct req_handler_wrapper
7564  {
7565  req_handler_wrapper(Func f)
7566  : f(std::move(f))
7567  {
7568  }
7569 
7570  void operator()(const request& req, response& res, Args... args)
7571  {
7572  res = response(f(req, args...));
7573  res.end();
7574  }
7575 
7576  Func f;
7577  };
7578 
7579  template <typename ... Args>
7580  void set(Func f, typename std::enable_if<
7581  std::is_same<typename std::tuple_element<0, std::tuple<Args..., void>>::type, const request&>::value &&
7582  !std::is_same<typename std::tuple_element<1, std::tuple<Args..., void, void>>::type, response&>::value
7583  , int>::type = 0)
7584  {
7585  handler_ = req_handler_wrapper<Args...>(std::move(f));
7586  /*handler_ = (
7587  [f = std::move(f)]
7588  (const request& req, response& res, Args... args){
7589  res = response(f(req, args...));
7590  res.end();
7591  });*/
7592  }
7593 
7594  template <typename ... Args>
7595  void set(Func f, typename std::enable_if<
7596  std::is_same<typename std::tuple_element<0, std::tuple<Args..., void>>::type, const request&>::value &&
7597  std::is_same<typename std::tuple_element<1, std::tuple<Args..., void, void>>::type, response&>::value
7598  , int>::type = 0)
7599  {
7600  handler_ = std::move(f);
7601  }
7602 
7603  template <typename ... Args>
7604  struct handler_type_helper
7605  {
7606  using type = std::function<void(const crow::request&, crow::response&, Args...)>;
7607  using args_type = black_magic::S<typename black_magic::promote_t<Args>...>;
7608  };
7609 
7610  template <typename ... Args>
7611  struct handler_type_helper<const request&, Args...>
7612  {
7613  using type = std::function<void(const crow::request&, crow::response&, Args...)>;
7614  using args_type = black_magic::S<typename black_magic::promote_t<Args>...>;
7615  };
7616 
7617  template <typename ... Args>
7618  struct handler_type_helper<const request&, response&, Args...>
7619  {
7620  using type = std::function<void(const crow::request&, crow::response&, Args...)>;
7621  using args_type = black_magic::S<typename black_magic::promote_t<Args>...>;
7622  };
7623 
7624  typename handler_type_helper<ArgsWrapped...>::type handler_;
7625 
7626  void operator()(const request& req, response& res, const routing_params& params)
7627  {
7628  detail::routing_handler_call_helper::call<
7629  detail::routing_handler_call_helper::call_params<
7630  decltype(handler_)>,
7631  0, 0, 0, 0,
7632  typename handler_type_helper<ArgsWrapped...>::args_type,
7633  black_magic::S<>
7634  >()(
7635  detail::routing_handler_call_helper::call_params<
7636  decltype(handler_)>
7637  {handler_, params, req, res}
7638  );
7639  }
7640  };
7641 
7642  }
7643  }

7710  template <typename T>
7711  struct RuleParameterTraits
7712  {
7713  using self_t = T;
7714  WebSocketRule& websocket()
7715  {
7716  auto p =new WebSocketRule(((self_t*)this)->rule_);
7717  ((self_t*)this)->rule_to_upgrade_.reset(p);
7718  return *p;
7719  }
7720 
7721  self_t& name(std::string name) noexcept
7722  {
7723  ((self_t*)this)->name_ = std::move(name);
7724  return (self_t&)*this;
7725  }
7726 
7727  self_t& methods(HTTPMethod method)
7728  {
7729  ((self_t*)this)->methods_ = 1 << (int)method;
7730  return (self_t&)*this;
7731  }
7732 
7733  template <typename ... MethodArgs>
7734  self_t& methods(HTTPMethod method, MethodArgs ... args_method)
7735  {
7736  methods(args_method...);
7737  ((self_t*)this)->methods_ |= 1 << (int)method;
7738  return (self_t&)*this;
7739  }
7740 
7741  };

7743  class DynamicRule : public BaseRule, public RuleParameterTraits<DynamicRule>
7744  {
7745  public:
7746 
7747  DynamicRule(std::string rule)
7748  : BaseRule(std::move(rule))
7749  {
7750  }
7751 
7752  void validate() override
7753  {
7754  if (!erased_handler_)
7755  {
7756  throw std::runtime_error(name_ + (!name_.empty() ? ": " : "") + "no handler for url " + rule_);
7757  }
7758  }
7759 
7760  void handle(const request& req, response& res, const routing_params& params) override
7761  {
7762  erased_handler_(req, res, params);
7763  }
7764 
7765  template <typename Func>
7766  void operator()(Func f)
7767  {
7768 #ifdef CROW_MSVC_WORKAROUND
7769  using function_t = utility::function_traits<decltype(&Func::operator())>;
7770 #else
7771  using function_t = utility::function_traits<Func>;
7772 #endif
7773  erased_handler_ = wrap(std::move(f), black_magic::gen_seq<function_t::arity>());
7774  }
7775 
7776  // enable_if Arg1 == request && Arg2 == response
7777  // enable_if Arg1 == request && Arg2 != resposne
7778  // enable_if Arg1 != request
7779 #ifdef CROW_MSVC_WORKAROUND
7780  template <typename Func, size_t ... Indices>
7781 #else
7782  template <typename Func, unsigned ... Indices>
7783 #endif
7784  std::function<void(const request&, response&, const routing_params&)>
7785  wrap(Func f, black_magic::seq<Indices...>)
7786  {
7787 #ifdef CROW_MSVC_WORKAROUND
7788  using function_t = utility::function_traits<decltype(&Func::operator())>;
7789 #else
7790  using function_t = utility::function_traits<Func>;
7791 #endif
7792  if (!black_magic::is_parameter_tag_compatible(
7793  black_magic::get_parameter_tag_runtime(rule_.c_str()),
7794  black_magic::compute_parameter_tag_from_args_list<
7795  typename function_t::template arg<Indices>...>::value))
7796  {
7797  throw std::runtime_error("route_dynamic: Handler type is mismatched with URL parameters: " + rule_);
7798  }
7799  auto ret = detail::routing_handler_call_helper::Wrapped<Func, typename function_t::template arg<Indices>...>();
7800  ret.template set<
7801  typename function_t::template arg<Indices>...
7802  >(std::move(f));
7803  return ret;
7804  }
7805 
7806  template <typename Func>
7807  void operator()(std::string name, Func&& f)
7808  {
7809  name_ = std::move(name);
7810  (*this).template operator()<Func>(std::forward(f));
7811  }
7812  private:
7813  std::function<void(const request&, response&, const routing_params&)> erased_handler_;
7814 
7815  };
7816 
7817  template <typename ... Args>
7818  class TaggedRule : public BaseRule, public RuleParameterTraits<TaggedRule<Args...>>
7819  {
7820  public:
7821  using self_t = TaggedRule<Args...>;
7822 
7823  TaggedRule(std::string rule)
7824  : BaseRule(std::move(rule))
7825  {
7826  }
7827 
7828  void validate() override
7829  {
7830  if (!handler_)
7831  {
7832  throw std::runtime_error(name_ + (!name_.empty() ? ": " : "") + "no handler for url " + rule_);
7833  }
7834  }
7835 
7836  template <typename Func>
7837  typename std::enable_if<black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<Args...>>::value, void>::type
7838  operator()(Func&& f)
7839  {
7840  static_assert(black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<Args...>>::value ||
7841  black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<crow::request, Args...>>::value ,
7842  "Handler type is mismatched with URL parameters");
7843  static_assert(!std::is_same<void, decltype(f(std::declval<Args>()...))>::value,
7844  "Handler function cannot have void return type; valid return types: string, int, crow::resposne, crow::json::wvalue");
7845 
7846  handler_ = [f = std::move(f)](const request&, response& res, Args ... args){
7847  res = response(f(args...));
7848  res.end();
7849  };
7850  }
7851 
7852  template <typename Func>
7853  typename std::enable_if<
7854  !black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<Args...>>::value &&
7855  black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<crow::request, Args...>>::value,
7856  void>::type
7857  operator()(Func&& f)
7858  {
7859  static_assert(black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<Args...>>::value ||
7860  black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<crow::request, Args...>>::value,
7861  "Handler type is mismatched with URL parameters");
7862  static_assert(!std::is_same<void, decltype(f(std::declval<crow::request>(), std::declval<Args>()...))>::value,
7863  "Handler function cannot have void return type; valid return types: string, int, crow::resposne, crow::json::wvalue");
7864 
7865  handler_ = [f = std::move(f)](const crow::request& req, crow::response& res, Args ... args){
7866  res = response(f(req, args...));
7867  res.end();
7868  };
7869  }
7870 
7871  template <typename Func>
7872  typename std::enable_if<
7873  !black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<Args...>>::value &&
7874  !black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<crow::request, Args...>>::value,
7875  void>::type
7876  operator()(Func&& f)
7877  {
7878  static_assert(black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<Args...>>::value ||
7879  black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<crow::request, Args...>>::value ||
7880  black_magic::CallHelper<Func, black_magic::S<crow::request, crow::response&, Args...>>::value
7881  ,
7882  "Handler type is mismatched with URL parameters");
7883  static_assert(std::is_same<void, decltype(f(std::declval<crow::request>(), std::declval<crow::response&>(), std::declval<Args>()...))>::value,
7884  "Handler function with response argument should have void return type");
7885 
7886  handler_ = std::move(f);
7887  }
7888 
7889  template <typename Func>
7890  void operator()(std::string name, Func&& f)
7891  {
7892  name_ = std::move(name);
7893  (*this).template operator()<Func>(std::forward(f));
7894  }
7895 
7896  void handle(const request& req, response& res, const routing_params& params) override
7897  {
7898  detail::routing_handler_call_helper::call<
7899  detail::routing_handler_call_helper::call_params<
7900  decltype(handler_)>,
7901  0, 0, 0, 0,
7902  black_magic::S<Args...>,
7903  black_magic::S<>
7904  >()(
7905  detail::routing_handler_call_helper::call_params<
7906  decltype(handler_)>
7907  {handler_, params, req, res}
7908  );
7909  }
7910 
7911  private:
7912  std::function<void(const crow::request&, crow::response&, Args...)> handler_;
7913 
7914  };
7915 
7916  const int RULE_SPECIAL_REDIRECT_SLASH = 1;
7917 
7918  class Trie
7919  {
7920  public:
7921  struct Node
7922  {
7923  unsigned rule_index{};
7924  std::array<unsigned, (int)ParamType::MAX> param_childrens{};
7925  std::unordered_map<std::string, unsigned> children;
7926 
7927  bool IsSimpleNode() const
7928  {
7929  return
7930  !rule_index &&
7931  std::all_of(
7932  std::begin(param_childrens),
7933  std::end(param_childrens),
7934  [](unsigned x){ return !x; });
7935  }
7936  };
7937 
7938  Trie() : nodes_(1)
7939  {
7940  }
7941 
7942 private:
7943  void optimizeNode(Node* node)
7944  {
7945  for(auto x : node->param_childrens)
7946  {
7947  if (!x)
7948  continue;
7949  Node* child = &nodes_[x];
7950  optimizeNode(child);
7951  }
7952  if (node->children.empty())
7953  return;
7954  bool mergeWithChild = true;
7955  for(auto& kv : node->children)
7956  {
7957  Node* child = &nodes_[kv.second];
7958  if (!child->IsSimpleNode())
7959  {
7960  mergeWithChild = false;
7961  break;
7962  }
7963  }
7964  if (mergeWithChild)
7965  {
7966  decltype(node->children) merged;
7967  for(auto& kv : node->children)
7968  {
7969  Node* child = &nodes_[kv.second];
7970  for(auto& child_kv : child->children)
7971  {
7972  merged[kv.first + child_kv.first] = child_kv.second;
7973  }
7974  }
7975  node->children = std::move(merged);
7976  optimizeNode(node);
7977  }
7978  else
7979  {
7980  for(auto& kv : node->children)
7981  {
7982  Node* child = &nodes_[kv.second];
7983  optimizeNode(child);
7984  }
7985  }
7986  }
7987 
7988  void optimize()
7989  {
7990  optimizeNode(head());
7991  }
7992 
7993 public:
7994  void validate()
7995  {
7996  if (!head()->IsSimpleNode())
7997  throw std::runtime_error("Internal error: Trie header should be simple!");
7998  optimize();
7999  }
8000 
8001  std::pair<unsigned, routing_params> find(const std::string& req_url, const Node* node = nullptr, unsigned pos = 0, routing_params* params = nullptr) const
8002  {
8003  routing_params empty;
8004  if (params == nullptr)
8005  params = &empty;
8006 
8007  unsigned found{};
8008  routing_params match_params;
8009 
8010  if (node == nullptr)
8011  node = head();
8012  if (pos == req_url.size())
8013  return {node->rule_index, *params};
8014 
8015  auto update_found = [&found, &match_params](std::pair<unsigned, routing_params>& ret)
8016  {
8017  if (ret.first && (!found || found > ret.first))
8018  {
8019  found = ret.first;
8020  match_params = std::move(ret.second);
8021  }
8022  };
8023 
8024  if (node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::INT])
8025  {
8026  char c = req_url[pos];
8027  if ((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || c == '+' || c == '-')
8028  {
8029  char* eptr;
8030  errno = 0;
8031  long long int value = strtoll(req_url.data()+pos, &eptr, 10);
8032  if (errno != ERANGE && eptr != req_url.data()+pos)
8033  {
8034  params->int_params.push_back(value);
8035  auto ret = find(req_url, &nodes_[node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::INT]], eptr - req_url.data(), params);
8036  update_found(ret);
8037  params->int_params.pop_back();
8038  }
8039  }
8040  }
8041 
8042  if (node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::UINT])
8043  {
8044  char c = req_url[pos];
8045  if ((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || c == '+')
8046  {
8047  char* eptr;
8048  errno = 0;
8049  unsigned long long int value = strtoull(req_url.data()+pos, &eptr, 10);
8050  if (errno != ERANGE && eptr != req_url.data()+pos)
8051  {
8052  params->uint_params.push_back(value);
8053  auto ret = find(req_url, &nodes_[node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::UINT]], eptr - req_url.data(), params);
8054  update_found(ret);
8055  params->uint_params.pop_back();
8056  }
8057  }
8058  }
8059 
8060  if (node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::DOUBLE])
8061  {
8062  char c = req_url[pos];
8063  if ((c >= '0' && c <= '9') || c == '+' || c == '-' || c == '.')
8064  {
8065  char* eptr;
8066  errno = 0;
8067  double value = strtod(req_url.data()+pos, &eptr);
8068  if (errno != ERANGE && eptr != req_url.data()+pos)
8069  {
8070  params->double_params.push_back(value);
8071  auto ret = find(req_url, &nodes_[node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::DOUBLE]], eptr - req_url.data(), params);
8072  update_found(ret);
8073  params->double_params.pop_back();
8074  }
8075  }
8076  }
8077 
8078  if (node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::STRING])
8079  {
8080  size_t epos = pos;
8081  for(; epos < req_url.size(); epos ++)
8082  {
8083  if (req_url[epos] == '/')
8084  break;
8085  }
8086 
8087  if (epos != pos)
8088  {
8089  params->string_params.push_back(req_url.substr(pos, epos-pos));
8090  auto ret = find(req_url, &nodes_[node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::STRING]], epos, params);
8091  update_found(ret);
8092  params->string_params.pop_back();
8093  }
8094  }
8095 
8096  if (node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::PATH])
8097  {
8098  size_t epos = req_url.size();
8099 
8100  if (epos != pos)
8101  {
8102  params->string_params.push_back(req_url.substr(pos, epos-pos));
8103  auto ret = find(req_url, &nodes_[node->param_childrens[(int)ParamType::PATH]], epos, params);
8104  update_found(ret);
8105  params->string_params.pop_back();
8106  }
8107  }
8108 
8109  for(auto& kv : node->children)
8110  {
8111  const std::string& fragment = kv.first;
8112  const Node* child = &nodes_[kv.second];
8113 
8114  if (req_url.compare(pos, fragment.size(), fragment) == 0)
8115  {
8116  auto ret = find(req_url, child, pos + fragment.size(), params);
8117  update_found(ret);
8118  }
8119  }
8120 
8121  return {found, match_params};
8122  }
8123 
8124  void add(const std::string& url, unsigned rule_index)
8125  {
8126  unsigned idx{0};
8127 
8128  for(unsigned i = 0; i < url.size(); i ++)
8129  {
8130  char c = url[i];
8131  if (c == '<')
8132  {
8133  static struct ParamTraits
8134  {
8135  ParamType type;
8136  std::string name;
8137  } paramTraits[] =
8138  {
8139  { ParamType::INT, "<int>" },
8140  { ParamType::UINT, "<uint>" },
8141  { ParamType::DOUBLE, "<float>" },
8142  { ParamType::DOUBLE, "<double>" },
8143  { ParamType::STRING, "<str>" },
8144  { ParamType::STRING, "<string>" },
8145  { ParamType::PATH, "<path>" },
8146  };
8147 
8148  for(auto& x:paramTraits)
8149  {
8150  if (url.compare(i, x.name.size(), x.name) == 0)
8151  {
8152  if (!nodes_[idx].param_childrens[(int)x.type])
8153  {
8154  auto new_node_idx = new_node();
8155  nodes_[idx].param_childrens[(int)x.type] = new_node_idx;
8156  }
8157  idx = nodes_[idx].param_childrens[(int)x.type];
8158  i += x.name.size();
8159  break;
8160  }
8161  }
8162 
8163  i --;
8164  }
8165  else
8166  {
8167  std::string piece(&c, 1);
8168  if (!nodes_[idx].children.count(piece))
8169  {
8170  auto new_node_idx = new_node();
8171  nodes_[idx].children.emplace(piece, new_node_idx);
8172  }
8173  idx = nodes_[idx].children[piece];
8174  }
8175  }
8176  if (nodes_[idx].rule_index)
8177  throw std::runtime_error("handler already exists for " + url);
8178  nodes_[idx].rule_index = rule_index;
8179  }
8180  private:
8181  void debug_node_print(Node* n, int level)
8182  {
8183  for(int i = 0; i < (int)ParamType::MAX; i ++)
8184  {
8185  if (n->param_childrens[i])
8186  {
8187  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << std::string(2*level, ' ') /*<< "("<<n->param_childrens[i]<<") "*/;
8188  switch((ParamType)i)
8189  {
8190  case ParamType::INT:
8191  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "<int>";
8192  break;
8193  case ParamType::UINT:
8194  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "<uint>";
8195  break;
8196  case ParamType::DOUBLE:
8197  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "<float>";
8198  break;
8199  case ParamType::STRING:
8200  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "<str>";
8201  break;
8202  case ParamType::PATH:
8203  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "<path>";
8204  break;
8205  default:
8206  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "<ERROR>";
8207  break;
8208  }
8209 
8210  debug_node_print(&nodes_[n->param_childrens[i]], level+1);
8211  }
8212  }
8213  for(auto& kv : n->children)
8214  {
8215  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << std::string(2*level, ' ') /*<< "(" << kv.second << ") "*/ << kv.first;
8216  debug_node_print(&nodes_[kv.second], level+1);
8217  }
8218  }
8219 
8220  public:
8221  void debug_print()
8222  {
8223  debug_node_print(head(), 0);
8224  }
8225 
8226  private:
8227  const Node* head() const
8228  {
8229  return &nodes_.front();
8230  }
8231 
8232  Node* head()
8233  {
8234  return &nodes_.front();
8235  }
8236 
8237  unsigned new_node()
8238  {
8239  nodes_.resize(nodes_.size()+1);
8240  return nodes_.size() - 1;
8241  }
8242 
8243  std::vector<Node> nodes_;
8244  };
