8246  class Router
8247  {
8248  public:
8249  Router() : rules_(2)
8250  {
8251  }
8252 
8253  DynamicRule& new_rule_dynamic(const std::string& rule)
8254  {
8255  auto ruleObject = new DynamicRule(rule);
8256 
8257  internal_add_rule_object(rule, ruleObject);
8258 
8259  return *ruleObject;
8260  }
8261 
8262  template <uint64_t N>
8263  typename black_magic::arguments<N>::type::template rebind<TaggedRule>& new_rule_tagged(const std::string& rule)
8264  {
8265  using RuleT = typename black_magic::arguments<N>::type::template rebind<TaggedRule>;
8266  auto ruleObject = new RuleT(rule);
8267 
8268  internal_add_rule_object(rule, ruleObject);
8269 
8270  return *ruleObject;
8271  }
8272 
8273  void internal_add_rule_object(const std::string& rule, BaseRule* ruleObject)
8274  {
8275  rules_.emplace_back(ruleObject);
8276  trie_.add(rule, rules_.size() - 1);
8277 
8278  // directory case:
8279  // request to `/about' url matches `/about/' rule
8280  if (rule.size() > 1 && rule.back() == '/')
8281  {
8282  std::string rule_without_trailing_slash = rule;
8283  rule_without_trailing_slash.pop_back();
8284  trie_.add(rule_without_trailing_slash, RULE_SPECIAL_REDIRECT_SLASH);
8285  }
8286  }
8287 
8288  void validate()
8289  {
8290  trie_.validate();
8291  for(auto& rule:rules_)
8292  {
8293  if (rule)
8294  {
8295  auto upgraded = rule->upgrade();
8296  if (upgraded)
8297  rule = std::move(upgraded);
8298  rule->validate();
8299  }
8300  }
8301  }
8302 
8303  template <typename Adaptor>
8304  void handle_upgrade(const request& req, response& res, Adaptor&& adaptor)
8305  {
8306  auto found = trie_.find(req.url);
8307  unsigned rule_index = found.first;
8308  if (!rule_index)
8309  {
8310  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Cannot match rules " << req.url;
8311  res = response(404);
8312  res.end();
8313  return;
8314  }
8315 
8316  if (rule_index >= rules_.size())
8317  throw std::runtime_error("Trie internal structure corrupted!");
8318 
8319  if (rule_index == RULE_SPECIAL_REDIRECT_SLASH)
8320  {
8321  CROW_LOG_INFO << "Redirecting to a url with trailing slash: " << req.url;
8322  res = response(301);
8323 
8324  // TODO absolute url building
8325  if (req.get_header_value("Host").empty())
8326  {
8327  res.add_header("Location", req.url + "/");
8328  }
8329  else
8330  {
8331  res.add_header("Location", "http://" + req.get_header_value("Host") + req.url + "/");
8332  }
8333  res.end();
8334  return;
8335  }
8336 
8337  if ((rules_[rule_index]->get_methods() & (1<<(uint32_t)req.method)) == 0)
8338  {
8339  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Rule found but method mismatch: " << req.url << " with " << method_name(req.method) << "(" << (uint32_t)req.method << ") / " << rules_[rule_index]->get_methods();
8340  res = response(404);
8341  res.end();
8342  return;
8343  }
8344 
8345  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Matched rule (upgrade) '" << rules_[rule_index]->rule_ << "' " << (uint32_t)req.method << " / " << rules_[rule_index]->get_methods();
8346 
8347  // any uncaught exceptions become 500s
8348  try
8349  {
8350  rules_[rule_index]->handle_upgrade(req, res, std::move(adaptor));
8351  }
8352  catch(std::exception& e)
8353  {
8354  CROW_LOG_ERROR << "An uncaught exception occurred: " << e.what();
8355  res = response(500);
8356  res.end();
8357  return;
8358  }
8359  catch(...)
8360  {
8361  CROW_LOG_ERROR << "An uncaught exception occurred. The type was unknown so no information was available.";
8362  res = response(500);
8363  res.end();
8364  return;
8365  }
8366  }
8367 
8368  void handle(const request& req, response& res)
8369  {
8370  auto found = trie_.find(req.url);
8371 
8372  unsigned rule_index = found.first;
8373 
8374  if (!rule_index)
8375  {
8376  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Cannot match rules " << req.url;
8377  res = response(404);
8378  res.end();
8379  return;
8380  }
8381 
8382  if (rule_index >= rules_.size())
8383  throw std::runtime_error("Trie internal structure corrupted!");
8384 
8385  if (rule_index == RULE_SPECIAL_REDIRECT_SLASH)
8386  {
8387  CROW_LOG_INFO << "Redirecting to a url with trailing slash: " << req.url;
8388  res = response(301);
8389 
8390  // TODO absolute url building
8391  if (req.get_header_value("Host").empty())
8392  {
8393  res.add_header("Location", req.url + "/");
8394  }
8395  else
8396  {
8397  res.add_header("Location", "http://" + req.get_header_value("Host") + req.url + "/");
8398  }
8399  res.end();
8400  return;
8401  }
8402 
8403  if ((rules_[rule_index]->get_methods() & (1<<(uint32_t)req.method)) == 0)
8404  {
8405  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Rule found but method mismatch: " << req.url << " with " << method_name(req.method) << "(" << (uint32_t)req.method << ") / " << rules_[rule_index]->get_methods();
8406  res = response(404);
8407  res.end();
8408  return;
8409  }
8410 
8411  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Matched rule '" << rules_[rule_index]->rule_ << "' " << (uint32_t)req.method << " / " << rules_[rule_index]->get_methods();
8412 
8413  // any uncaught exceptions become 500s
8414  try
8415  {
8416  rules_[rule_index]->handle(req, res, found.second);
8417  }
8418  catch(std::exception& e)
8419  {
8420  CROW_LOG_ERROR << "An uncaught exception occurred: " << e.what();
8421  res = response(500);
8422  res.end();
8423  return;
8424  }
8425  catch(...)
8426  {
8427  CROW_LOG_ERROR << "An uncaught exception occurred. The type was unknown so no information was available.";
8428  res = response(500);
8429  res.end();
8430  return;
8431  }
8432  }
8433 
8434  void debug_print()
8435  {
8436  trie_.debug_print();
8437  }
8438 
8439  private:
8440  std::vector<std::unique_ptr<BaseRule>> rules_;
8441  Trie trie_;
8442  };
8443 }

8571  >
8572  struct get

8581  >
8582  struct get

8585 
8586  template <typename T>
8587  struct is_before_handle_arity_3_impl
8588  {
8589  template <typename C>
8590  static std::true_type f(typename check_before_handle_arity_3_const<T>::template get<C>*);
8591 
8592  template <typename C>
8593  static std::true_type f(typename check_before_handle_arity_3<T>::template get<C>*);
8594 
8595  template <typename C>
8596  static std::false_type f(...);
8597 
8598  public:
8599  static const bool value = decltype(f<T>(nullptr))::value;
8600  };
8601 
8602  template <typename T>
8603  struct is_after_handle_arity_3_impl
8604  {
8605  template <typename C>
8606  static std::true_type f(typename check_after_handle_arity_3_const<T>::template get<C>*);
8607 
8608  template <typename C>
8609  static std::true_type f(typename check_after_handle_arity_3<T>::template get<C>*);
8610 
8611  template <typename C>
8612  static std::false_type f(...);
8613 
8614  public:
8615  static const bool value = decltype(f<T>(nullptr))::value;
8616  };
8617 
8618  template <typename MW, typename Context, typename ParentContext>
8619  typename std::enable_if<!is_before_handle_arity_3_impl<MW>::value>::type
8620  before_handler_call(MW& mw, request& req, response& res, Context& ctx, ParentContext& /*parent_ctx*/)
8621  {
8622  mw.before_handle(req, res, ctx.template get<MW>(), ctx);
8623  }
8624 
8625  template <typename MW, typename Context, typename ParentContext>
8626  typename std::enable_if<is_before_handle_arity_3_impl<MW>::value>::type
8627  before_handler_call(MW& mw, request& req, response& res, Context& ctx, ParentContext& /*parent_ctx*/)
8628  {
8629  mw.before_handle(req, res, ctx.template get<MW>());
8630  }
8631 
8632  template <typename MW, typename Context, typename ParentContext>
8633  typename std::enable_if<!is_after_handle_arity_3_impl<MW>::value>::type
8634  after_handler_call(MW& mw, request& req, response& res, Context& ctx, ParentContext& /*parent_ctx*/)
8635  {
8636  mw.after_handle(req, res, ctx.template get<MW>(), ctx);
8637  }
8638 
8639  template <typename MW, typename Context, typename ParentContext>
8640  typename std::enable_if<is_after_handle_arity_3_impl<MW>::value>::type
8641  after_handler_call(MW& mw, request& req, response& res, Context& ctx, ParentContext& /*parent_ctx*/)
8642  {
8643  mw.after_handle(req, res, ctx.template get<MW>());
8644  }
8645 
8646  template <int N, typename Context, typename Container, typename CurrentMW, typename ... Middlewares>
8647  bool middleware_call_helper(Container& middlewares, request& req, response& res, Context& ctx)
8648  {
8649  using parent_context_t = typename Context::template partial<N-1>;
8650  before_handler_call<CurrentMW, Context, parent_context_t>(std::get<N>(middlewares), req, res, ctx, static_cast<parent_context_t&>(ctx));
8651 
8652  if (res.is_completed())
8653  {
8654  after_handler_call<CurrentMW, Context, parent_context_t>(std::get<N>(middlewares), req, res, ctx, static_cast<parent_context_t&>(ctx));
8655  return true;
8656  }
8657 
8658  if (middleware_call_helper<N+1, Context, Container, Middlewares...>(middlewares, req, res, ctx))
8659  {
8660  after_handler_call<CurrentMW, Context, parent_context_t>(std::get<N>(middlewares), req, res, ctx, static_cast<parent_context_t&>(ctx));
8661  return true;
8662  }
8663 
8664  return false;
8665  }
8666 
8667  template <int N, typename Context, typename Container>
8668  bool middleware_call_helper(Container& /*middlewares*/, request& /*req*/, response& /*res*/, Context& /*ctx*/)
8669  {
8670  return false;
8671  }
8672 
8673  template <int N, typename Context, typename Container>
8674  typename std::enable_if<(N<0)>::type
8675  after_handlers_call_helper(Container& /*middlewares*/, Context& /*context*/, request& /*req*/, response& /*res*/)
8676  {
8677  }
8678 
8679  template <int N, typename Context, typename Container>
8680  typename std::enable_if<(N==0)>::type after_handlers_call_helper(Container& middlewares, Context& ctx, request& req, response& res)
8681  {
8682  using parent_context_t = typename Context::template partial<N-1>;
8683  using CurrentMW = typename std::tuple_element<N, typename std::remove_reference<Container>::type>::type;
8684  after_handler_call<CurrentMW, Context, parent_context_t>(std::get<N>(middlewares), req, res, ctx, static_cast<parent_context_t&>(ctx));
8685  }
8686 
8687  template <int N, typename Context, typename Container>
8688  typename std::enable_if<(N>0)>::type after_handlers_call_helper(Container& middlewares, Context& ctx, request& req, response& res)
8689  {
8690  using parent_context_t = typename Context::template partial<N-1>;
8691  using CurrentMW = typename std::tuple_element<N, typename std::remove_reference<Container>::type>::type;
8692  after_handler_call<CurrentMW, Context, parent_context_t>(std::get<N>(middlewares), req, res, ctx, static_cast<parent_context_t&>(ctx));
8693  after_handlers_call_helper<N-1, Context, Container>(middlewares, ctx, req, res);
8694  }
8695  }
8696 
8697 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_DEBUG
8698  static int connectionCount;
8699 #endif
8700  template <typename Adaptor, typename Handler, typename ... Middlewares>
8701  class Connection
8702  {
8703  public:
8704  Connection(
8705  boost::asio::io_service& io_service,
8706  Handler* handler,
8707  const std::string& server_name,
8708  std::tuple<Middlewares...>* middlewares,
8709  std::function<std::string()>& get_cached_date_str_f,
8710  detail::dumb_timer_queue& timer_queue,
8711  typename Adaptor::context* adaptor_ctx_
8712  )
8713  : adaptor_(io_service, adaptor_ctx_),
8714  handler_(handler),
8715  parser_(this),
8716  server_name_(server_name),
8717  middlewares_(middlewares),
8718  get_cached_date_str(get_cached_date_str_f),
8719  timer_queue(timer_queue)
8720  {
8721 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_DEBUG
8722  connectionCount ++;
8723  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Connection open, total " << connectionCount << ", " << this;
8724 #endif
8725  }
8726 
8727  ~Connection()
8728  {
8729  res.complete_request_handler_ = nullptr;
8730  cancel_deadline_timer();
8731 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_DEBUG
8732  connectionCount --;
8733  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << "Connection closed, total " << connectionCount << ", " << this;
8734 #endif
8735  }
8736 
8737  decltype(std::declval<Adaptor>().raw_socket())& socket()
8738  {
8739  return adaptor_.raw_socket();
8740  }
8741 
8742  void start()
8743  {
8744  adaptor_.start([this](const boost::system::error_code& ec) {
8745  if (!ec)
8746  {
8747  start_deadline();
8748 
8749  do_read();
8750  }
8751  else
8752  {
8753  check_destroy();
8754  }
8755  });
8756  }
8757 
8758  void handle_header()
8759  {
8760  // HTTP 1.1 Expect: 100-continue
8761  if (parser_.check_version(1, 1) && parser_.headers.count("expect") && get_header_value(parser_.headers, "expect") == "100-continue")
8762  {
8763  buffers_.clear();
8764  static std::string expect_100_continue = "HTTP/1.1 100 Continue\r\n\r\n";
8765  buffers_.emplace_back(expect_100_continue.data(), expect_100_continue.size());
8766  do_write();
8767  }
8768  }
8769 
8770  void handle()
8771  {
8772  cancel_deadline_timer();
8773  bool is_invalid_request = false;
8774  add_keep_alive_ = false;
8775 
8776  req_ = std::move(parser_.to_request());
8777  request& req = req_;
8778 
8779  if (parser_.check_version(1, 0))
8780  {
8781  // HTTP/1.0
8782  if (req.headers.count("connection"))
8783  {
8784  if (boost::iequals(req.get_header_value("connection"),"Keep-Alive"))
8785  add_keep_alive_ = true;
8786  }
8787  else
8788  close_connection_ = true;
8789  }
8790  else if (parser_.check_version(1, 1))
8791  {
8792  // HTTP/1.1
8793  if (req.headers.count("connection"))
8794  {
8795  if (req.get_header_value("connection") == "close")
8796  close_connection_ = true;
8797  else if (boost::iequals(req.get_header_value("connection"),"Keep-Alive"))
8798  add_keep_alive_ = true;
8799  }
8800  if (!req.headers.count("host"))
8801  {
8802  is_invalid_request = true;
8803  res = response(400);
8804  }
8805  if (parser_.is_upgrade())
8806  {
8807  if (req.get_header_value("upgrade") == "h2c")
8808  {
8809  // TODO HTTP/2
8810  // currently, ignore upgrade header
8811  }
8812  else
8813  {
8814  close_connection_ = true;
8815  handler_->handle_upgrade(req, res, std::move(adaptor_));
8816  return;
8817  }
8818  }
8819  }
8820 
8821  CROW_LOG_INFO << "Request: " << boost::lexical_cast<std::string>(adaptor_.remote_endpoint()) << " " << this << " HTTP/" << parser_.http_major << "." << parser_.http_minor << ' '
8822  << method_name(req.method) << " " << req.url;
8823 
8824 
8825  need_to_call_after_handlers_ = false;
8826  if (!is_invalid_request)
8827  {
8828  res.complete_request_handler_ = []{};
8829  res.is_alive_helper_ = [this]()->bool{ return adaptor_.is_open(); };
8830 
8831  ctx_ = detail::context<Middlewares...>();
8832  req.middleware_context = (void*)&ctx_;
8833  req.io_service = &adaptor_.get_io_service();
8834  detail::middleware_call_helper<0, decltype(ctx_), decltype(*middlewares_), Middlewares...>(*middlewares_, req, res, ctx_);
8835 
8836  if (!res.completed_)
8837  {
8838  res.complete_request_handler_ = [this]{ this->complete_request(); };
8839  need_to_call_after_handlers_ = true;
8840  handler_->handle(req, res);
8841  if (add_keep_alive_)
8842  res.set_header("connection", "Keep-Alive");
8843  }
8844  else
8845  {
8846  complete_request();
8847  }
8848  }
8849  else
8850  {
8851  complete_request();
8852  }
8853  }
8854 
8855  void complete_request()
8856  {
8857  CROW_LOG_INFO << "Response: " << this << ' ' << req_.raw_url << ' ' << res.code << ' ' << close_connection_;
8858 
8859  if (need_to_call_after_handlers_)
8860  {
8861  need_to_call_after_handlers_ = false;
8862 
8863  // call all after_handler of middlewares
8864  detail::after_handlers_call_helper<
8865  ((int)sizeof...(Middlewares)-1),
8866  decltype(ctx_),
8867  decltype(*middlewares_)>
8868  (*middlewares_, ctx_, req_, res);
8869  }
8870 
8871  //auto self = this->shared_from_this();
8872  res.complete_request_handler_ = nullptr;
8873 
8874  if (!adaptor_.is_open())
8875  {
8876  //CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " delete (socket is closed) " << is_reading << ' ' << is_writing;
8877  //delete this;
8878  return;
8879  }
8880 
8881  static std::unordered_map<int, std::string> statusCodes = {
8882  {200, "HTTP/1.1 200 OK\r\n"},
8883  {201, "HTTP/1.1 201 Created\r\n"},
8884  {202, "HTTP/1.1 202 Accepted\r\n"},
8885  {204, "HTTP/1.1 204 No Content\r\n"},
8886 
8887  {300, "HTTP/1.1 300 Multiple Choices\r\n"},
8888  {301, "HTTP/1.1 301 Moved Permanently\r\n"},
8889  {302, "HTTP/1.1 302 Moved Temporarily\r\n"},
8890  {304, "HTTP/1.1 304 Not Modified\r\n"},
8891 
8892  {400, "HTTP/1.1 400 Bad Request\r\n"},
8893  {401, "HTTP/1.1 401 Unauthorized\r\n"},
8894  {403, "HTTP/1.1 403 Forbidden\r\n"},
8895  {404, "HTTP/1.1 404 Not Found\r\n"},
8896 
8897  {500, "HTTP/1.1 500 Internal Server Error\r\n"},
8898  {501, "HTTP/1.1 501 Not Implemented\r\n"},
8899  {502, "HTTP/1.1 502 Bad Gateway\r\n"},
8900  {503, "HTTP/1.1 503 Service Unavailable\r\n"},
8901  };
8902 
8903  static std::string seperator = ": ";
8904  static std::string crlf = "\r\n";
8905 
8906  buffers_.clear();
8907  buffers_.reserve(4*(res.headers.size()+5)+3);
8908 
8909  if (res.body.empty() && res.json_value.t() == json::type::Object)
8910  {
8911  res.body = json::dump(res.json_value);
8912  }
8913 
8914  if (!statusCodes.count(res.code))
8915  res.code = 500;
8916  {
8917  auto& status = statusCodes.find(res.code)->second;
8918  buffers_.emplace_back(status.data(), status.size());
8919  }
8920 
8921  if (res.code >= 400 && res.body.empty())
8922  res.body = statusCodes[res.code].substr(9);
8923 
8924  for(auto& kv : res.headers)
8925  {
8926  buffers_.emplace_back(kv.first.data(), kv.first.size());
8927  buffers_.emplace_back(seperator.data(), seperator.size());
8928  buffers_.emplace_back(kv.second.data(), kv.second.size());
8929  buffers_.emplace_back(crlf.data(), crlf.size());
8930 
8931  }
8932 
8933  if (!res.headers.count("content-length"))
8934  {
8935  content_length_ = std::to_string(res.body.size());
8936  static std::string content_length_tag = "Content-Length: ";
8937  buffers_.emplace_back(content_length_tag.data(), content_length_tag.size());
8938  buffers_.emplace_back(content_length_.data(), content_length_.size());
8939  buffers_.emplace_back(crlf.data(), crlf.size());
8940  }
8941  if (!res.headers.count("server"))
8942  {
8943  static std::string server_tag = "Server: ";
8944  buffers_.emplace_back(server_tag.data(), server_tag.size());
8945  buffers_.emplace_back(server_name_.data(), server_name_.size());
8946  buffers_.emplace_back(crlf.data(), crlf.size());
8947  }
8948  if (!res.headers.count("date"))
8949  {
8950  static std::string date_tag = "Date: ";
8951  date_str_ = get_cached_date_str();
8952  buffers_.emplace_back(date_tag.data(), date_tag.size());
8953  buffers_.emplace_back(date_str_.data(), date_str_.size());
8954  buffers_.emplace_back(crlf.data(), crlf.size());
8955  }
8956  if (add_keep_alive_)
8957  {
8958  static std::string keep_alive_tag = "Connection: Keep-Alive";
8959  buffers_.emplace_back(keep_alive_tag.data(), keep_alive_tag.size());
8960  buffers_.emplace_back(crlf.data(), crlf.size());
8961  }
8962 
8963  buffers_.emplace_back(crlf.data(), crlf.size());
8964  res_body_copy_.swap(res.body);
8965  buffers_.emplace_back(res_body_copy_.data(), res_body_copy_.size());
8966 
8967  do_write();
8968 
8969  if (need_to_start_read_after_complete_)
8970  {
8971  need_to_start_read_after_complete_ = false;
8972  start_deadline();
8973  do_read();
8974  }
8975  }
8976 
8977  private:
8978  void do_read()
8979  {
8980  //auto self = this->shared_from_this();
8981  is_reading = true;
8982  adaptor_.socket().async_read_some(boost::asio::buffer(buffer_),
8983  [this](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t bytes_transferred)
8984  {
8985  bool error_while_reading = true;
8986  if (!ec)
8987  {
8988  bool ret = parser_.feed(buffer_.data(), bytes_transferred);
8989  if (ret && adaptor_.is_open())
8990  {
8991  error_while_reading = false;
8992  }
8993  }
8994 
8995  if (error_while_reading)
8996  {
8997  cancel_deadline_timer();
8998  parser_.done();
8999  adaptor_.close();
9000  is_reading = false;
9001  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " from read(1)";
9002  check_destroy();
9003  }
9004  else if (close_connection_)
9005  {
9006  cancel_deadline_timer();
9007  parser_.done();
9008  is_reading = false;
9009  check_destroy();
9010  // adaptor will close after write
9011  }
9012  else if (!need_to_call_after_handlers_)
9013  {
9014  start_deadline();
9015  do_read();
9016  }
9017  else
9018  {
9019  // res will be completed later by user
9020  need_to_start_read_after_complete_ = true;
9021  }
9022  });
9023  }
9024 
9025  void do_write()
9026  {
9027  //auto self = this->shared_from_this();
9028  is_writing = true;
9029  boost::asio::async_write(adaptor_.socket(), buffers_,
9030  [&](const boost::system::error_code& ec, std::size_t /*bytes_transferred*/)
9031  {
9032  is_writing = false;
9033  res.clear();
9034  res_body_copy_.clear();
9035  if (!ec)
9036  {
9037  if (close_connection_)
9038  {
9039  adaptor_.close();
9040  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " from write(1)";
9041  check_destroy();
9042  }
9043  }
9044  else
9045  {
9046  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " from write(2)";
9047  check_destroy();
9048  }
9049  });
9050  }
9051 
9052  void check_destroy()
9053  {
9054  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " is_reading " << is_reading << " is_writing " << is_writing;
9055  if (!is_reading && !is_writing)
9056  {
9057  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " delete (idle) ";
9058  delete this;
9059  }
9060  }
9061 
9062  void cancel_deadline_timer()
9063  {
9064  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " timer cancelled: " << timer_cancel_key_.first << ' ' << timer_cancel_key_.second;
9065  timer_queue.cancel(timer_cancel_key_);
9066  }
9067 
9068  void start_deadline(/*int timeout = 5*/)
9069  {
9070  cancel_deadline_timer();
9071 
9072  timer_cancel_key_ = timer_queue.add([this]
9073  {
9074  if (!adaptor_.is_open())
9075  {
9076  return;
9077  }
9078  adaptor_.close();
9079  });
9080  CROW_LOG_DEBUG << this << " timer added: " << timer_cancel_key_.first << ' ' << timer_cancel_key_.second;
9081  }
9082

9122 #pragma once
9123 
9124 #include <chrono>
9125 #include <boost/date_time/posix_time/posix_time.hpp>
9126 #include <boost/asio.hpp>
9127 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_SSL
9128 #include <boost/asio/ssl.hpp>
9129 #endif
9130 #include <cstdint>
9131 #include <atomic>
9132 #include <future>
9133 #include <vector>
9134 
9135 #include <memory>

9143 
9144 namespace crow
9145 {
9146  using namespace boost;
9147  using tcp = asio::ip::tcp;
9148 
9149  template <typename Handler, typename Adaptor = SocketAdaptor, typename ... Middlewares>
9150  class Server
9151  {
9152  public:
9153  Server(Handler* handler, std::string bindaddr, uint16_t port, std::tuple<Middlewares...>* middlewares = nullptr, uint16_t concurrency = 1, typename Adaptor::context* adaptor_ctx = nullptr)
9154  : acceptor_(io_service_, tcp::endpoint(boost::asio::ip::address::from_string(bindaddr), port)),
9155  signals_(io_service_, SIGINT, SIGTERM),
9156  tick_timer_(io_service_),
9157  handler_(handler),
9158  concurrency_(concurrency),
9159  port_(port),
9160  bindaddr_(bindaddr),
9161  middlewares_(middlewares),
9162  adaptor_ctx_(adaptor_ctx)
9163  {
9164  }
9165 
9166  void set_tick_function(std::chrono::milliseconds d, std::function<void()> f)
9167  {
9168  tick_interval_ = d;
9169  tick_function_ = f;
9170  }
9171 
9172  void on_tick()
9173  {
9174  tick_function_();
9175  tick_timer_.expires_from_now(boost::posix_time::milliseconds(tick_interval_.count()));
9176  tick_timer_.async_wait([this](const boost::system::error_code& ec)
9177  {
9178  if (ec)
9179  return;
9180  on_tick();
9181  });
9182  }
9183 
9184  void run()
9185  {
9186  if (concurrency_ < 0)
9187  concurrency_ = 1;
9188 
9189  for(int i = 0; i < concurrency_; i++)
9190  io_service_pool_.emplace_back(new boost::asio::io_service());
9191  get_cached_date_str_pool_.resize(concurrency_);
9192  timer_queue_pool_.resize(concurrency_);
9193 
9194  std::vector<std::future<void>> v;
9195  std::atomic<int> init_count(0);
9196  for(uint16_t i = 0; i < concurrency_; i ++)
9197  v.push_back(
9198  std::async(std::launch::async, [this, i, &init_count]{
9199 
9200  // thread local date string get function
9201  auto last = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
9202 
9203  std::string date_str;
9204  auto update_date_str = [&]
9205  {
9206  auto last_time_t = time(0);
9207  tm my_tm;
9208 
9209 #ifdef _MSC_VER
9210  gmtime_s(&my_tm, &last_time_t);
9211 #else
9212  gmtime_r(&last_time_t, &my_tm);
9213 #endif
9214  date_str.resize(100);
9215  size_t date_str_sz = strftime(&date_str[0], 99, "%a, %d %b %Y %H:%M:%S GMT", &my_tm);
9216  date_str.resize(date_str_sz);
9217  };
9218  update_date_str();
9219  get_cached_date_str_pool_[i] = [&]()->std::string
9220  {
9221  if (std::chrono::steady_clock::now() - last >= std::chrono::seconds(1))
9222  {
9223  last = std::chrono::steady_clock::now();
9224  update_date_str();
9225  }
9226  return date_str;
9227  };
9228 
9229  // initializing timer queue
9230  detail::dumb_timer_queue timer_queue;
9231  timer_queue_pool_[i] = &timer_queue;
9232 
9233  timer_queue.set_io_service(*io_service_pool_[i]);
9234  boost::asio::deadline_timer timer(*io_service_pool_[i]);
9235  timer.expires_from_now(boost::posix_time::seconds(1));
9236 
9237  std::function<void(const boost::system::error_code& ec)> handler;
9238  handler = [&](const boost::system::error_code& ec){
9239  if (ec)
9240  return;
9241  timer_queue.process();
9242  timer.expires_from_now(boost::posix_time::seconds(1));
9243  timer.async_wait(handler);
9244  };
9245  timer.async_wait(handler);
9246 
9247  init_count ++;
9248  try
9249  {
9250  io_service_pool_[i]->run();
9251  } catch(std::exception& e)
9252  {
9253  CROW_LOG_ERROR << "Worker Crash: An uncaught exception occurred: " << e.what();
9254  }
9255  }));
9256 
9257  if (tick_function_ && tick_interval_.count() > 0)
9258  {
9259  tick_timer_.expires_from_now(boost::posix_time::milliseconds(tick_interval_.count()));
9260  tick_timer_.async_wait([this](const boost::system::error_code& ec)
9261  {
9262  if (ec)
9263  return;
9264  on_tick();
9265  });
9266  }
9267 
9268  CROW_LOG_INFO << server_name_ << " server is running, local port " << port_;
9269 
9270  signals_.async_wait(
9271  [&](const boost::system::error_code& /*error*/, int /*signal_number*/){
9272  stop();
9273  });
9274 
9275  while(concurrency_ != init_count)
9276  std::this_thread::yield();
9277 
9278  do_accept();
9279 
9280  std::thread([this]{
9281  io_service_.run();
9282  CROW_LOG_INFO << "Exiting.";
9283  }).join();
9284  }
9285 
9286  void stop()
9287  {
9288  io_service_.stop();
9289  for(auto& io_service:io_service_pool_)
9290  io_service->stop();
9291  }
9292 
9293  private:
9294  asio::io_service& pick_io_service()
9295  {
9296  // TODO load balancing
9297  roundrobin_index_++;
9298  if (roundrobin_index_ >= io_service_pool_.size())
9299  roundrobin_index_ = 0;
9300  return *io_service_pool_[roundrobin_index_];
9301  }
9302 
9303  void do_accept()
9304  {
9305  asio::io_service& is = pick_io_service();
9306  auto p = new Connection<Adaptor, Handler, Middlewares...>(
9307  is, handler_, server_name_, middlewares_,
9308  get_cached_date_str_pool_[roundrobin_index_], *timer_queue_pool_[roundrobin_index_],
9309  adaptor_ctx_);
9310  acceptor_.async_accept(p->socket(),
9311  [this, p, &is](boost::system::error_code ec)
9312  {
9313  if (!ec)
9314  {
9315  is.post([p]
9316  {
9317  p->start();
9318  });
9319  }
9320  do_accept();
9321  });
9322  }
9323 
9324  private:
9325  asio::io_service io_service_;
9326  std::vector<std::unique_ptr<asio::io_service>> io_service_pool_;
9327  std::vector<detail::dumb_timer_queue*> timer_queue_pool_;
9328  std::vector<std::function<std::string()>> get_cached_date_str_pool_;
9329  tcp::acceptor acceptor_;
9330  boost::asio::signal_set signals_;
9331  boost::asio::deadline_timer tick_timer_;
9332 
9333  Handler* handler_;
9334  uint16_t concurrency_{1};
9335  std::string server_name_ = "Crow/0.1";
9336  uint16_t port_;
9337  std::string bindaddr_;
9338  unsigned int roundrobin_index_{};
9339 
9340  std::chrono::milliseconds tick_interval_;
9341  std::function<void()> tick_function_;
9342 
9343  std::tuple<Middlewares...>* middlewares_;
9344 
9345 #ifdef CROW_ENABLE_SSL
9346  bool use_ssl_{false};
9347  boost::asio::ssl::context ssl_context_{boost::asio::ssl::context::sslv23};
9348 #endif
9349  typename Adaptor::context* adaptor_ctx_;
9350  };
9351 }
